title: pumpkin-nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, corn oil and eggs.
Sift together salt, flour, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda.
Alternate 2/3 cup water and dry ingredients to creamed batter.
Fold in pumpkin, pecans and raisins.
Flour and grease 3 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: spanish meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Divide mixture into 4 parts and shape into loaves.
Place in baking dish and bake for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Pour boiling water over strawberries.
Let stand 2 minutes; drain.
Add 4 cups sugar to each quart of strawberries and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
When bubbling stops, add 2 cups sugar to each quart of berries.
Let stand overnight.
Pour into jars. Must be kept in cool place.

title: italian pepper biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil to yeast and water; pour into flour mixture.
Mix well.
Knead slightly, cover and let rise for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Knead a few times and divide dough.
Roll into "snakes" about the size of a pencil approximately 18 inches long.
Cut in half and twist together. Pinch into a circle.
Let sit 15 minutes.
Place on baking sheet sprayed with Pam and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or so.
If baking two sheets together, alternate at "half-time". Enjoy!

title: dawn's chicken strips
directions: Debone chicken.
Cut into strips, about 1-inch wide.
Mix milk, salt, egg and wine together in a bowl.
Marinate chicken strips in mixture overnight.
Remove chicken from liquid and roll in pancake flour.
Fry in deep fat fryer until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot or cold.
Add more salt, if desired.

title: aloha cake
directions: Following directions on cake mix, mix up.
Pour into greased and floured large jelly roll pan and bake.
In a bowl, mix together Dream Whip following directions on box.
Add pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Spread over top of cooled cake.
Drain pineapple well.
Sprinkle on top of cream mixture.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup coconut, 1/2 cup nuts and dot with maraschino cherries.
Chill.
Keeps well for 3 to 4 days in refrigerator.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat well.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until limp; drain the grease from pan.
Add beans with juice, tomatoes with juice and spices.
Simmer while you mix the cornbread batter.
Adjust the seasoning and pour into a large pan.
Cover with thin layer of cornbread batter.
(If you have more batter than needed to cover, bake in separate pan.)
Bake until cornbread is done.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cooking Time: 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order. Pour into unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie shells.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 to 50 minutes or until center is cooked.
Cool. Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut bread into cubes; place in a large, shallow pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until toasted.
Spray a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with nonstick spray coating.
Place half of the bread cubes in the baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage, sweet pepper and mushrooms until sausage is brown.
Drain off fat.
Pat vegetable mixture with a paper towel.
Spoon mixture atop bread cubes in dish.
Sprinkle with half of the shredded cheese.
Top with remaining bread.
In mixing bowl, mix soup, egg product, evaporated milk, mustard and pepper.
Pour over bread, pressing down cubes with the back of a spoon to moisten.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours or up to 24 hours.
To serve, bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 3 minutes longer; let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together softened margarine, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Layer over graham cracker mix. Arrange banana slices on top.
Cover with crushed pineapple.
Cover with topping.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: quill's teriyaki marinade for two steaks
directions: Crush garlic in a cup or small bowl and set aside.
Slice ginger root into 3 slices about the thickness of a silver dollar. Crush.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the first 8 ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, pumpkin and water and mix with beater.
Add nuts and dates.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine 1 cup cracker crumbs with remaining ingredients, except egg whites.
Shape salmon mixture into patties.
Put on cookie sheet and put in freezer for about 1 hour; do not freeze. Take out.
Beat egg whites; dip patties in egg whites, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat.

title: quick quick brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt together over low heat the cocoa and butter.
Remove from heat. Add sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix well and pour into pan.
Top with nuts.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line bottom of cookie sheet and sides with aluminum foil. Then put layer of graham crackers to cover bottom. Mix butter, margarine and sugar in sauce pan and when it comes to a boil...boil for 3 minutes. Pour over graham crackers and put chopped pecans on top of mixture. Place in 350° oven and bake for 17 minutes. When cool break into pieces.

title: deep dish apple cranberry
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and apple pie filling together; set aside. Mix the rest of the ingredients together; put mixture in a Pyrex dish, then pour in filling and sauce.
Put the rest of the ingredients from sugar and oatmeal on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and gravy roast
directions: Place roast in a deep baking dish.
Pour soup over top of roast, then sprinkle dried onion soup mix on top of soup.
Add 2 soup cans of water around sides of roast.
Cover and bake at 300° for about 3 hours.

title: cajun crawfish
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers in cooking oil.
Add Tony's seasoning.
After sauteing, add flour to thicken.
Stir in well. Add tomato sauce and water.
Stir well.
Let cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Then add crawfish; lower heat and let cook for 30 minutes.
May add crab meat when crawfish is added, if desired; serve over rice.

title: apple butter
directions: Put in large roasting pan and bake for 3 hours at 350°.
Stir every 15 minutes with a wooden spoon.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Form into 1 1/2-inch thick steak.
Rub with margarine.
Broil 12 minutes on one side and 10 minutes on the other.

title: jello and cool whip easy strawberry trifle
directions: Stir 1 1/2 cups boiling water in strawberry Jell-O in a large bowl until completely dissolved. Stir in 1 1/2 cups cold water. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Cut into squares (cubes). Layer cubes, pound cake (cut into cubes like Jell-O), 1/2 tub Cool Whip and 2 cups of sliced strawberries in a large glass bowl. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate 1 hour. Makes 15 servings.

title: jamaican chicken fricassee
directions: Wash and cut up chicken.
Marinate in above ingredients in refrigerator
for several hours.
Heat 1/5 cup oil in large frying pan.
Brown
chicken
pieces.
Do	not
cover.
Remove chicken from
pan,	leaving oil in pan.
Pour marinade liquid, onion slices
and chopped tomato into frying pan.
Add 3/4 cup water. Place
browned
chicken
pieces in pan. Cover and cook until liquid thickens with gravy. Serve with Jamaican Peas and Rice.

title: barbecue oriental chicken
directions: Place chicken in dish.
Sprinkle with spices.
Pour soy sauce and peanut oil over chicken.
Cover with tight-fitting lid.
Shake until chicken is well-saturated.
Place in refrigerator.
Light coals in grill.
Occasionally shake chicken while marinating.
When coals are grey (45 minutes to 1 hour), place chicken on grill. Cook over medium heat about 1 1/4 hours.
Baste occasionally with remaining marinade.
Discard remaining marinade.
Serve chicken on a bed of steamed rice and garnish with pineapple slices if desired.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, milk and sugar in small mixing bowl with a fork. Melt butter on griddle.
Dip bread into egg mixture.
Cook until golden brown.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage for 5 minutes.
Form meat balls with ground beef; roll in rice.
Drop meat balls in boiling cabbage.
Cook 5 minutes and add the rest of ingredients.
Cook for at least 1 hour, covered, over medium heat.

title: orange-orange cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and egg.
Add orange juice and orange rind.
Then add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Glaze immediately from oven.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Wash and pick over rice.

title: quick chili sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in heavy skillet; bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes. Mix sugar, spices and salt. Add with vinegar to first mixture. Simmer, stirring often, 30 minutes or until thick. Makes 4 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: easy salsa dip
directions: Mix all until smooth.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve cold with tortilla chips.

title: man made broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli in unsalted water. Drain and place in a baking dish.
Combine soup and cheese.
Add milk, mayonnaise and egg and pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand about 20 minutes before serving.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate for 2 hours.
Cook on outdoor grill, covered with aluminum foil, until done.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients above and set aside. Just before you are ready to serve, add dressing.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain green beans and white corn.
Then mix all ingredients, except Ritz crackers and butter into large baking dish.
Crumble up 1 tube Ritz crackers over top of vegetables.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes (until the top is golden brown).

title: white gravy
directions: Cook bacon or sausage in frying pan.
Sift in heaping tablespoonfuls of flour into saved grease, stirring the whole time so lumps won't form.
Brown flour.
Add milk.
Add water.
Salt to taste (add a little and then taste until you get it like you like it).
Cook over medium heat until gravy thickens.

title: frito and chili
directions: Grease a 2 qt. casserole dish. Add Fritos and pour chili on top. Put onion over chili. Sprinkle cheese on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sunshine frosting
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on freshly baked cake of your choice.
Frosting is delicious and holds up very well.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar, milk and egg yolks over medium heat, stirring constantly, until starting to thicken.
Add egg yolks, vanilla, butter and toasted coconut.
Pour in pie crust and top with egg white meringue and toasted coconut.

title: california walnut bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups walnuts.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix just until ingredients are moistened and blended. Turn into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in bowl; set aside.
Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Add flour mixture, a little at a time, until all blended.
Add M&M's and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: candy balls
directions: Melt 2 sticks butter and mix all ingredients together.
Roll out into balls.
Melt 1 bag chocolate chips and 1/2 block paraffin wax.
Melt in a double boiler.
Dip candy balls into chocolate and lay on wax paper.

title: lemon herb basting sauce for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in shaker and shake well.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cook in crock-pot, uncovered, for 8 hours.

title: spinach bars
directions: Mix eggs, cottage cheese, 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and garlic; blend well.
Mix in drained spinach.
Put in no-stick or sprayed pan and put the 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Better to bake too long than too little.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Mix together.
Roll out on floured board to desired thickness. Cut in pieces about 2 or 3 inches long.
I cook them in broth from pot roast.

title: swedish dessert
directions: Crumble crackers. Beat egg whites. Add sugar, nuts, crackers, vanilla and salt. Put in pie dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool completely. Whip 1/2 pint whipping cream. Spread on top of pie and grate chocolate bar on top. Chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together chicken, broth, soup and vegetables.
Spread evenly in greased oblong casserole dish.
Mix together flour, milk and melted butter.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 400° or until crust is golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Alternate layers of potatoes, onion and butter in greased baking dish. Mix flour, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over potatoes. Bake for 90 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in oven for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt oleo.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over oleo.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over ingredients evenly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl until consistency is somewhat smooth (there will be lumps).
With a spatula, spread approximately 1/4-inch thick layer of spread to cover tortilla, then tightly roll up tortilla.
Repeat as far as mixture goes. Wrap them in cello wrap and refrigerate a few hours or overnight. Remove and slice into 1 to 1 1/2-inch lengths.
Turn on their sides and serve on platter with side of salsa.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk together. Fold in whipped topping.
Put mixture into crust and freeze.
Take out of freezer about 30 minutes before serving.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add milk and pudding to creamed mixture.
Mix well, then add whipped topping.
Grind cookies in a food processor or blender. In a clean flower pot, layer mixtures, alternating cream and crumbs, ending with a layer of crumbs on top.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain fruit real good.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Put in saucepan and let come to boil.
Pour over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and whip until fluffy.
Put in refrigerator until thick.
When thickened, fold in fruit and Cool Whip.

title: nancy's waffles
directions: Mix together with a wire whisk, adding oleo last.
Use a waffle iron.
So rich you won't have to use butter!

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix melted butter with graham cracker crumbs and press into Pam coated 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream 2 cubes butter (softened) with powdered sugar.
Beat in eggs; mix for no less than 15 minutes. Spread mixture over crumbs.
Add sliced bananas and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with cherries and pecans.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Mix, heat and stir into vegetables all remaining ingredients.

title: promiseland stuffed deer hindquarter
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stuff hindquarter with ingredients and tie shut with cooking string. Grill on
high heat for 1 hour until meat is brown.
Place a pan of water over flame and boil for moisture.
Let cook for 15 minutes, slice 1 inch thick and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing after each.
In separate bowl, mix buttermilk and soda.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk mixture, mixing well.
Add mashed bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Divide mixture into three loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion and green pepper. Combine remaining ingredients except cheese; blend well. Add onion and green pepper.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes until firm and set.

title: beer-batter fried fish
directions: Mix together flour, beer, egg, Tabasco sauce, oil and 1 teaspoon salt.
Let stand at least 20 minutes.
Heat oil in deep-fat fryer to 375°.
Stir batter to remix.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper, dip in batter and fry, turning once, until golden brown.
Drain fish on paper towels.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook until mixture begins to thicken, then put in cooked pie crust.
Use whites of eggs for topping.
Put in oven until meringue browns.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken pieces into egg and roll in mixture of crumbs, cheese, garlic and salt.
Coat well.
Arrange chicken in microwavable 2-quart dish with larger pieces at corners, skin side up.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes (or until chicken is done and tender) in microwave/convection oven at 7 Combination power or at 425° for 45 minutes in oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into ball and chill.
You can roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Put potato chips in plastic bag.
Close the bag tightly. Crush chips.
Pour into pie plate.
Put butter or margarine in skillet.
Melt.
Stir in salt and pepper until well mixed.
Brush chicken with butter mixture.
Roll in potato chips until well coated.
Bake about 50 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together in a bowl.
Pour into prepared loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sand dessert
directions: You will need a sand bucket and shovel.

title: crab and broccoli
directions: Drain broccoli and break into chunks.
Bake with other ingredients in a shallow, buttered casserole at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Separate crescent roll dough into 8 triangles.
Put 5 triangles in 9-inch pie plate, pressing together to form crust.

title: lemon-caper chicken
directions: Heat oil.
Flour chicken and brown.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Add salt and pepper to pan.
Add capers and lemon juice. Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add bouillon; cook and stir for 1 minute. Put chicken back in and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add water as needed to prevent from going dry.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef and vegetable fried rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef, garlic and ginger over medium heat, 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix will be crumbly.
Drain beef of oil. Put in bowl; set aside.
In same skillet, heat vegetable oil. Stir in pepper and pea pods for 3 minutes or until crisp-tender. Add rice, soy sauce and sesame oil.
Mix well.
Add beef; heat about 5 minutes.
Stir in onion.
Garnish as desired.
Makes four 1 1/2-cup servings.

title: almond cookies
directions: Mix the lard, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, almond and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture and beat until well mixed.
Dough will be rather dry and crumbly. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Brush top with well beaten egg using pastry brush.
Press blanched almonds into each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes on greased cookie sheets.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Heat butter, marshmallows, cocoa and Coca-Cola together.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Put soda in milk and ingredients.
Bake in long pan or 2 round pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate crunch cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and butter.
Add cereal; stir until well blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Dip a fork in flour and flatten cookie in crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: chicken and cheese lasagna
directions: Heat butter in heavy, large saucepan and add garlic and onion. Stir in flour and salt.
Cook stirring constantly until bubbly. Stir in milk and broth slowly.
Heat to boil.
Boil 1 minute stirring constantly.
Add cheeses (save 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese). Add spices.
Stir until cheeses melt.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer in the following order:

1/4 cheese sauce, noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/4 cheese sauce, noodles, remaining cottage cheese, chicken and spinach, cheese sauce, noodles and remaining cheese sauce; sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Wait 15 minutes before serving.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and cream well.
Slowly add flour to creamed mixture. Stir until smooth.
Use your hands to press the dough into 9-inch shortbread mold or a 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pan.
Run a knife around edge of pan to loosen. Turn out onto serving plate. Cut into wedges and serve.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Blend cake mix, oil and softened margarine in large bowl. Beat in one egg at a time, then beat according to cake mix box directions.
Fold in sour cream and nuts.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle the sugar and cinnamon evenly over batter.
Pour the remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Turn out on cake plate and pour on milk glaze while still warm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Blend cake mix, oil and eggs until moistened.
Add juice from can of oranges and mix.
Stir orange slices into mixture gently. Bake at 350° in 3 layer cake pans for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill until set.

title: yellow rice with chicken
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Add meat and brown well on both sides.
Add onion, garlic and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and water.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in bay leaf, Vego and rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until tender.
Garnish with English peas.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: You will also need rock salt or crumbled foil.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt and sugar.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once. Blend just until flour is all moistened.
Refrigerate as mixture will be soft.
Ready to roll out when you can press firmly into a ball.

title: sweet potato custard pie
directions: Beat yolks until thick.
Gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form.
Fold into sweet potato mixture.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: rhubarb conserve
directions: Cut up rhubarb.
Put lemons and oranges through food processor.
Do not peel.
Remove seeds.
Mix all with sugar.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, let cool until it thickens.
Add nuts.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 9 baking dish at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes (until top is golden).
Serve warm from the oven with wheat thin style crackers.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix buttermilk with sugar to dissolve crystals.
Add salt and vanilla and freeze until mushy.
Whip and fold in Cool Whip. Freeze.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Mix egg in a wide soup bowl with salt, pepper, onion powder and garlic powder.
Place bread crumbs in a wide soup bowl and dip meat on both sides in the egg mix.
Roll meat in bread crumbs on both sides.
Place in a heated oil frying pan on medium heat, all pieces, with tight-fitting cover for a few minutes and turn over; put cover on and cook on slow heat until done (5 minutes).
Turn again if needed.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast, salt and sugar, then add lukewarm water and cooled shortening (be sure shortening is cool).
Keep adding flour to right consistency.
Knead a few times until elastic.
Then roll out on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cook at 400°.
Makes about 15 rolls.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Add egg yolks to mashed potatoes and mix well.
Add the flour and baking powder alternately with milk until smooth.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites and drop by spoonful on hot greased griddle or skillet.
Chopped onion is sometimes sprinkled on the batter on griddle before turning.
Serve hot with meat.

title: english pea salad
directions: Open English peas and drain all water off. Pour into bowl. Add Hellmann's mayonnaise, diced pickles, chopped onions and diced boiled eggs. Stir all together.
This is very quick and easy and very tasty.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Toss together oil, salt, pepper and hash browns.
Line pie pan with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown. While baking, brown the ground beef.
Add the Veg-All, BV sauce and soy sauce.
Mix flour into Veg-All juice.
Add half the cheese and 1/4 cup French fried onions and mix together.
Pour on top of potatoes.
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle the rest of the cheese and onions on top.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Fold in eggs.
Mix in bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together and quickly beat into other ingredients.
Chop dates and pecans; flour lightly and add to mixture.
Turn into a greased loaf pan and let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: red bean and rice salad
directions: Combine sausage and 1 cup vinegar in a nonreactive saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes, or until sausage is cooked through.
Remove sausage from vinegar; cut into 1-inch pieces and set aside.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing with your hands.
Shape into five 4 x 1-inch rolls.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
This mixture will be very dry.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and water.
Pour mixture into a pan greased with butter.
Pour berries into the mixture. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and peanut butter over medium heat until mixture boils.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, marshmallows and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Drop on buttered tin.

title: heavenly sin
directions: Mix flour and margarine; pat firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar; spread over crust.
Make instant pudding, use less milk than stated on the box.
Spread pudding on top.
Refrigerate.

title: batter for onion rings
directions: Add the milk, a little at a time (should be like pancakes). It is easier to try one and, if the batter is too thick, then thin it, rather than to thin to start with.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.
Great with ham.

title: refrigerator cheese cake
directions: Dissolve lemon Jello in boiling water, then set aside.
Be sure it is completely cooled at room temperature, but not jelled.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Stir together 1/4 cup sugar and the gelatin in saucepan; stir in strawberries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture boils.
Place pan in bowl of ice and water or chill in refrigerator, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.

title: japanese fried rice(becky's favorite)
directions: Whip the eggs. Cook in lightly greased skillet, making very thin pancakes (about 4).
Remove, roll up and slice thinly.
This is garnish for dish.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt the 1/2 stick of oleo in a medium sized casserole dish. Mix all the ingredients together and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and bacon; add celery and onion.
Mix all others. Bake in a 2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
Put grated cheese on top the last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: ribs
directions: Parboil ribs in a little water with onion, celery, peppercorns and salt, about 20 minutes.
Drain ribs.
Place on a rack in shallow pan.
Set oven at 375°.
Mix rest of ingredients (except lemons) together and spread over ribs.
Lay sliced lemon on top.
Cook until ribs are crisp and sauce is sticky, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and season; cut into bite sizes.
Cook macaroni in salted water and drain.
Thicken chicken broth with flour. Cook a few minutes.
Add diced cheese and soup.
Mix well and add to chicken.
Brown bread crumbs in margarine, pour over top and cook 30 minutes at 325°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter on low heat.
Stir in brown sugar and cool.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: strawberry pastries
directions: Roll each sheet of dough out to about 12 x 6-inches.
If desired, sift powdered sugar over counter before rolling.
Cut each sheet into 4 even pieces.
Cover baking sheets with waxed paper. Place dough on prepared sheet.
Prick with fork.
Sift powdered sugar over dough.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for about 5 minutes; increase oven to 450°, bake another 3 to 5 minutes until pastries are light golden and puffed.
Let cool on wire rack. In heavy saucepan bring half and half to boil.
Cook over medium-low heat about 10 minutes.
Remove, add vanilla.
In a bowl, beat egg yolks and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add a little hot half and half, whisking, then pour this mixture into saucepan. Bring to a boil, whisking constantly until thick and creamy.
Do not boil or custard will curdle.
Remove custard sauce from heat. Beat until cool.
Whip cream until soft peaks form.
Add to vanilla custard.
Spread over half of the baked pastries.
Cover with sliced strawberries.
Top with second half of pastries.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Serves 12.

title: mike's banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in top of double boiler; slowly stir in hot milk and cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly. Stir a little of the hot mixture into beaten egg yolks. Pour back into double boiler. Cook about 2 more minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla and cool until just warm. Alternate layers of vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding in a baking dish. Beat egg whites until foamy; add 1/4 cup sugar gradually. Beat until stiff. Pile lightly on pudding. Bake in hot 400° oven for 8 minutes or until golden.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Shred meat.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Saute onion in margarine, then blend in flour, soup and milk for sauce.
Drain mushrooms and add to sauce.
Add salt and pepper.
In a very large casserole dish (or 1 large and 1 medium), layer with sauce, rice, chicken and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: classic pumpkin pie with candied pecan topping
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, granulated sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, salt, ginger, nutmeg and cloves in large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake for 1 hour 10 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely.
Grease baking sheet lightly with shortening.
For topping; combine granulated sugar and water in small saucepan.
Cook and stir on medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 7 to 8 minutes or until mixture becomes light golden brown, stirring frequently. Stir in butter and nuts.
Stir briskly.
Spread quickly in thin layer on baking sheet.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces. Sprinkle around edge of pie.
Refrigerate leftover pie.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix hamburger or ground beef, sausage, rice and seasonings; set aside.

title: garlic soup
directions: Boil garlic in water.
Drain off water.
Add same amount of potatoes and cover slightly with chicken broth.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Pour into blender and blend until creamy. Pour into serving bowls and serve with croutons.
May garnish with freshly chopped parsley.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil together; add eggs.
Drain pineapple and save 2 tbsp. juice for the icing.
Add remaining juice and pineapple to creamed mixture.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add to pineapple mixture with the vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350 degrees for 30-45 minutes.
For icing, melt cream cheese and butter over low heat.
Add reserved pineapple juice and enough powdered sugar to make spreadable.
Beat well to remove any lumps.
Pour over hot cake.

title: macaroni and cheese pita(makaronopita)
directions: Cook elbow macaroni
in
boiling,
salted
water
until almost done.
Drain well.	Beat
eggs
well.
Add milk and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Mix macaroni with cheeses and stir lightly to mix.
Add to eggs and
milk.	Salt
to
taste.
Stir	well. Carefully line 9 x 13-inch
pan
(which
has been greased with melted butter) with 8 sheets
of
filo; brush each with melted butter.	Pour mixture into
pan.	Top with additional 8 sheets filo.
Brush each with butter.
Sprinkle
with water or milk. Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes,
then
lower to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: elaine's apple cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
Cream next 4 ingredients.
Add cream mixture to flour.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: idaho spud cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Add alternately with milk.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°
for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Frost with Granny's Good Frosting.

title: brunch bubble ring
directions: Grease 12-cup Bundt pan.
Combine first three ingredients in small bowl and mix well.
Separate biscuit dough; cut each biscuit in half.

title: syrup pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in unbaked pie shell.

title: whipped buttercream icing
directions: Beat granulated sugar, meringue and water to a thick meringue; set aside.
Cream together Crisco, vanilla, powdered sugar, salt and butter flavoring.
Cream well together, then add first half mixture.
Beat well.
Add second half and beat well (do not underbeat).
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.
Can be used to decorate cakes.

title: 14k cake(makes 3 layers)
directions: Measure and sift together twice.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients (except marshmallows).
Mix thoroughly; may be a little lumpy.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with marshmallows last 10 minutes.

title: cheese-and-olive tea sandwiches
directions: About 1 hour before serving or early in the day, in a medium bowl, mix the first 4 ingredients.
Trim crusts from bread slices. (Save crusts to use for bread crumbs another day.)
Lightly spread 1 side of each bread slice with butter or margarine. Spread filling on 8 buttered bread slices; top with remaining bread slices, butter side down.
Cut each sandwich diagonally into quarters.
Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan with damp paper towels.
Place tea sandwiches in jelly roll pan. Cover with damp paper towels to keep bread from drying out.
Cover pan with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 32 tea sandwiches.
Contains about 60 calories each.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion, celery and salt and pepper to taste.
Grease a deep pie plate and put meat mixture in it.
Add cheese on top.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Pour over meat mixture and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: postre de coco(coconut dessert)
directions: Out of the 2 quarts of milk, set aside 1/2 cup.
In this little bit of milk, mix the cornstarch and set aside.
Place the grated coconut, the cold milk and the sugar in your blender and blend. Break up the egg yolks.
Place the coconut milk, the dissolved cornstarch and egg yolks in a saucepan and stir continuously over heat until it comes to a boil.
When it boils, add the evaporated milk and then set aside.
In a separate container, beat the egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup water; heat until it dissolves, stirring constantly.
When totally dissolved, add to the egg whites while stirring.
Add this mixture to the previously prepared coconut milk.
Mix everything thoroughly.

title: dill dressing
directions: Crush the dill seed in a bowl.
Add the dry ingredients and mix.
Add vinegar; stir until the sugar dissolves.
Mix in the oil.
Place the dill sprig in a pint jar.
Pour in the dressing. Keep covered in the refrigerator.

title: cherry delite
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with canned cherry or blueberry pie filling.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together.
Cook until done.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green chilies in pan.
Add enchilada sauce (mild and hot), cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Cook until comes to a boil.
Cover bottom of pan with chips and pour mixture over chips.
Add cheese on top.
Put in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: spiced pineapple tea
directions: Combine pineapple juice, apple, sugar and cinnamon in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add tea bags; steep 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add more flour if needed to make workable dough.
Take lump of dough about the size of a grapefruit and roll it out very thin.
Cut into strips about 2 x 6-inch (accuracy not important).
In center of each strip, cut about 1 1/2-inch slit lengthwise.
Turn one end through the slit.
Fry in oil (half gallon for single batch or 1 gallon if it is doubled).

When they are first put in oil, they will sink; as they fry, they will float. When they are floating, flip them over so they brown on both sides. When browned, remove from oil and let them cool and dry on brown paper (grocery shopping bag).
When dry and cool, sprinkle powdered sugar on them.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: gouie chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When cake is done, punch holes all over top of cake with a fork.
Drizzle the Eagle Brand milk over top. Pour jar of caramel sauce over top of milk; spread.
Sprinkle top with nuts (optional).
Spread a small amount of Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate.

title: california cheese soup
directions: Bring water to boil in large kettle.
Add the next 6 ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until all vegetables are tender, approximately 30 minutes.
Stir in soup and cheese.
Cook until soup is heated through and the cheese is melted.
Makes 3 quarts, about 10 to 12 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Season hamburger and put in casserole.
Add 1 can mushroom soup and milk.
Place 4 slices cheese on top.
Top with Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Grease a casserole dish and set aside.
Beat egg and then mix with milk.
Add sugar and flour.
Stir (do not beat), stirring constantly.
Slowly add peaches.
Spread evenly in casserole dish and then sprinkle the cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until browned.

title: fast fixin' chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan and stir with a fork or spoon until blended. Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: cheese and cherry dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix graham crackers, butter and 1/4 cup sugar together.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat down evenly. Bake for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool thoroughly. Combine cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Add 1 cup sugar; beat well.
Set aside.
Prepare whipped topping as directed on package.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over graham crackers.
Spoon pie filling over this and chill 2 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and heat to boiling, then use for any recipe calling for barbecue sauce.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix crackers, melted butter and sugar. Press into a pie plate. Beat cheese until fluffy. Add milk. Beat until well mixed. Add lemon and vanilla until well blended. Put in pie crust and chill for 2 to 3 hours. Do not freeze. At serving time, top with pie filling.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in greased casserole.
Top with butter and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: nearly brownie cookies
directions: Melt 8 ounces chocolate and butter over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla at high speed until well combined in separate bowl.
Slowly beat in the cooled chocolate into egg mixture, then add dry ingredients until just blended but smooth.
Stir in the chocolate chips and the nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 1 inch apart on cookie sheet covered with parchment paper or aluminum foil.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Don't overbake.

title: macaroni-cheese casserole
directions: Combine macaroni, cheese, 1 cup of the cracker crumbs, mushroom soup, mushrooms, milk, onion and green pepper.
Turn mixture into 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 325° until hot, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve hard-cooked eggs lengthwise; remove yolks and mash with salad dressing, mustard, salt and pepper.
Refill whites.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: borsch
directions: You will need a 6-quart soup pot.
In a separate pot, wash neck bones.
Cover with cold water, bring to a boil, drain and wash soup pot.
Pour cold water to fill the pot 3/4 full.
Bring to a boil; skim off the foam until clean.
Add celery, carrots, parsley root and leaves, onion, bay leaf, peppercorns and garlic clove.
Simmer 2 hours.
Let cool and strain into other pot.
Pick off meat from bones and add to stock.
Refrigerate overnight. Skim off fat.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Mix pineapple (less 1/2 cup) with sour cream.
Add package instant pudding and mix.
Pour in baked pie shell and top with Cool Whip.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter or margarine.
Let this cool.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook in greased pie plate (or tinfoil plate) at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine and corn syrup in medium size saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla extract and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies cereal, mixing lightly until well coated.
Spread evenly in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, which has been buttered.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt chocolate.
Grease baking pan. Cream butter in bowl; add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time to mixture.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Add chocolate, vanilla and flour.
Add nuts and stir enough to mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pinwheels(cookies)
directions: Beat butter until light.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Add to butter. Mix well.
Divide dough in half.
Mix chocolate into one-half. Wrap both halves in plastic; chill for several hours.
Roll out plain and chocolate dough separately into oblongs, 1/8-inch thick. Place dark dough on top of light.
Roll up layers together. Wrap.
Chill overnight.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets; cut roll into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Bake 8 minutes. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter in mixing bowl until light. Add confectioners sugar, gradually, beating until fluffy. Stir in cereal.
Shape by level tablespoonfuls into logs. Roll in peanuts. Place on waxed paper.
Melt the chocolate chips and shortening in a double boiler over hot water, stirring constantly. Drizzle over logs.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: carolyn's cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In heavy saucepan, bring the water and butter to a full, rolling boil.
Stir in flour all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture leaves the edges of the pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Beat until smooth and velvety.

title: pilgrim pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix until smooth and place in pie shell. Bake at 400° on cookie sheet on lower shelf in oven until knife inserted in filling comes out clean, about 40 minutes.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes. Cut in inch cubes. Bring water to boil. Add potatoes. Cook until tender. Measure 1 cup of liquid (add water, if necessary). Set aside. Chop onion (finely). Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat. Add onion. Cook, stirring frequently, until onion is translucent. Add flour to saucepan. Season with peppers. Cook 3 to 4 minutes. Gradually add potatoes, reserved 1 cup liquid, milk and sugar to onion mix. Stir well. Add cheese and ham. Simmer over low heat about 30 minutes.

title: sarah's tuna casserole
directions: Add ingredients to cooked noodles with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Mix together.
Pour into large Pyrex pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with rest of cheese.
Add the potato chips.
Cook at 350° until bubbly and browned.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels and milk in top of double boiler.
Add chopped pecans.
Drop this onto waxed paper (by spoonfuls).
Melt Hershey bar and paraffin in double boiler.

title: banana chocolate chip bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars. Beat in eggs, vanilla and bananas. Add flour and soda. Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zesty cauliflower
directions: Serve hot as a side vegetable, or at room temperature as an appetizer.

title: mystery salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges, reserving liquid.
Mix pineapple, mandarin oranges, bananas and marshmallows.
Mix reserved liquid with pudding mix.
Pour pudding mixture over fruit mixture.
Chill or serve immediately.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Combine pudding, oleo, cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk. Add
Cool
Whip
last;
beat with beater.
(Set aside.) Then crush Oreo cookies.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown pork sausage and drain.
Melt Velveeta in double broiler and mix with browned and drained pork sausage.
Stir in other four ingredients.
Spread on slices of party rye and put in 350 - 375 degree oven for 5 to 10 minutes till bubbly.
Makes about 40 pizzas.

title: dill salad
directions: Mix
cabbage,
grapes, apples and pecans.
Mix Sweet 'N Low with Miracle Whip and add to other ingredients.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain sliced peaches, oranges and pineapple chunks well.
Into a large bowl, put entire contents of peach pie filling and strawberries.
Mix.
Stir in well drained fruit.
Slice bananas and stir in.
Chill for 6 to 8 hours.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter.
Add garlic and parsley.
Add shrimp; saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add wine.
Continue to cook shrimp for 5 minutes over a low heat until shrimp is pink.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix starch in water.
In double boiler, blend sugar and salt. Add remainder of water.
When well mixed, stir over boiling water 10 minutes.
Pour mixture slowly over beaten egg yolks, stirring all the time.
Return to cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Mix well.
Cool. Pour into pie shell. Top with meringue and bake until brown.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Chill ingredients.
Freeze in ice cream churn.	Makes 4 quarts.

title: ez peanut butter kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine peanut butter, egg and sugar. Stir by hand until creamy.
Add flour.
Stir until flour is completely mixed in.
Roll into balls that are approximately the size of a quarter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press Hershey's Kiss into each ball and press down to secure and flatten cookie.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes approximately 2 dozen cookies.
I always double this recipe!

title: low-fat creamy seafood dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
In blender or food processor, blend cheeses and next 3 ingredients until smooth. Stir in onions and seafood.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: chicken orange
directions: Flour chicken thighs and breasts and brown in butter.
Place in casserole dish.
Cut up green onions and place in butter and fry until soft.
Add mushrooms, soy sauce, vermouth, honey, water and rind.
Stir.
Then pour over chicken.
Add up to 1 cup water. Cover dish and bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix good with hands.
Roll into small balls.
Fry in deep fryer.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients, then add this mixture to 1 cup boiling water.
Add vegetable oil and food color of choice. Cook, stirring constantly, for 3 to 4 minutes until it forms a ball.
Store in the refrigerator in a plastic bag or airtight container.

title: aunt frances' chocolate pie(best in the world!)
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, flour, cornstarch, salt and milk in large cooking pan.
Stir over medium heat until thick and smooth. Turn off heat.
Mix a cupful of the pudding with the beaten eggs. Return cup of pudding to pan; heat again for 8 minutes, until all is cooked through, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.
Melt the margarine and real vanilla in pudding.
Pour into baked pie shell and cool.
Top with real whipped cream and chocolate curls.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the brown sugar and nuts; spread on top of batter.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Boil until clear and thick. Add jello.
Mix well and cool.
Add strawberries.
Pour into prepared crusts.
Chill. Top with Cool Whip.

title: salami
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add water and liquid smoke.
Mix well. Divide in 2 portions, making 2 rolls 2 to 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll in foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Unroll and bake on rack 1 hour at 350°.
Shut off oven and leave in oven 20 minutes to drain fat.
Roll in new foil.
Slice as desired, when wanted.

title: country pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Mix buttermilk, margarine and eggs.
Pour over yolk mixture, then over the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Fry in medium hot skillet or griddle.

title: teriyaki bar-b-que sauce
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a sauce pan.
Bring to a boil. Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir slowly into boiling mixture to thicken sauce.

title: bob barber's gourmet hot dogs
directions: Place hot dogs in boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes or in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes until they explode.
Add ketchup, mustard, relish and onion to taste.

title: popovers for two
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and mix until smooth. Place 4 well-greased muffin cups in oven at 425° for 3 minutes or until water sizzles when dropped on them. Remove cups from oven and fill half full with batter. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 20 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 4 popovers.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets; let cool and then peel.
Slice beets; put into mixture and bring to boil.
Put hot mixture into hot jars and seal.

title: blueberry crunch "oh so good"
directions: Pour undrained pineapple in bottom of 8 x 12 inch baking dish. Layer blueberries, sugar, cake mix, margarine, pecans, and sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Put peanut butter in glass Pyrex cup and place in hot water to melt.
Take 1/2 cup melted peanut butter and add to chocolate melted on stove.
Place 1 tablespoon chocolate mixture into paper cupcake liners (cut down to 1/2 tablespoon if desired).
Put 1 tablespoon melted peanut butter on top, then 1 tablespoon chocolate mixture.
Freeze or refrigerate to harden.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Blend oleo, Crisco, cocoa and Coke.
Bring to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken banana curry from south africa
directions: Grate onion; saute in butter.
Add curry and fry 1 minute. Add mashed bananas, tomatoes, sugar and salt and cook.
Stir in flour and slowly add chicken stock, milk and cream, stirring constantly until thick.
Add lemon and tomato juice.
Fold in 2 cups cooked chicken chunks and heat thoroughly.
Serve with white rice and buttered thin bread slices.
Unusual and delicious dish.

title: hungarian pork(makes 6 servings)
directions: Pound the pork slices lightly with a flat mallet.
Sprinkle them with salt and pepper.
Dredge them in the flour.
Heat the oil in a large frying pan and when it is hot, add the pork slices. Cook for 2 minutes on each side.
Transfer the pork slices to a serving plate and keep them warm.

title: one pan chocolate coconut bars
directions: Melt butter in oblong baking dish.
Layer each of the remaining ingredients, beginning with graham cracker crumbs and topping with Eagle Brand.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cut while warm.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add vanilla and gradually add sugar.
Combine the salt, baking powder and flour together.
Add oil and flour mixture alternately into the eggs.
Blend well.
Place more than half of batter into 9-inch square, greased and floured cake pan. Add sliced apples over the batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg, then pour the rest of the batter over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: kielbasa and cabbage
directions: Cook the bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Add next 7 ingredients to drippings; cover and cook for 10 minutes over medium heat, turning cabbage once.
Add sausage; cover and cook 5 minutes or until sausage is heated.
Sprinkle bacon over the cabbage; cover and let steam for 10 minutes.
Transfer to a serving dish.

title: eggplant caviar
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and eggplant; saute for 2 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce and garlic; simmer over low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally, until eggplant is no longer chewy.
Check to be sure no browning occurs on the bottom of pan.
When mixture is very thick and vegetables are done, remove from heat.
Add salt, pepper, hot pepper sauce and lemon juice to taste.
Cover and chill.
To serve, sprinkle with fresh parsley and tomato.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers, removing inner membranes and seeds.
Parboil peppers for 5 minutes.
In large bowl, combine meat, seasonings, chopped onion, rice and egg.
In saucepan, mix tomato sauce and consomme; heat.
Add one cup sauce mix to meat and rice mixture. Stuff the peppers.
Use remaining sauce mix to pour over stuffed peppers.
Bake at 350° in uncovered (oiled dish) for 60 minutes. Serve with garlic bread.

title: brandy raisin-apple pie
directions: Combine raisins and brandy, cover and refrigerate overnight, drain and set aside.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often until well mixed (2 or 3 minutes).
Add bananas and orange juice.
Continue beating until well mixed.
By hand, stir in coconut and nuts.
Spread into three greased 5 1/2 x 3-inch mini pans or one greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake mini loaves at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
In 9 x 5-inch pan, bake 60 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: hot vegetable dish
directions: Drain potatoes, onions, green beans and mushrooms.
Combine with soup.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until heated through.
Add cubed ham, if desired. Yields 12 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in carrots, coconut and pineapple. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Frost cake when cool and refrigerate.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix together.
Keep dry in airtight container.
Can be used as gifts when put in decorative jars.
To make the tea use 2 to 3 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: nutty marshmallow delight
directions: Cut thawed dough into 16 pieces.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Dip each marshmallow into margarine and then into cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Wrap each marshmallow with a piece of dough and seal edges.
Dip into margarine and then into cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Grease Bundt pan or cake pan.
Sprinkle a few nuts.
Arrange marshmallow balls in 2 rows in pan.
Sprinkle any remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture on top.
Let rise until doubled in size (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Turn out onto serving plate.

title: frypan cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add dates, sugar and egg.
Cook on stove over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, walnuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.
Cool on cookie sheet.

title: chili
directions: Mix and simmer 45 minutes.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls in hot oil.

title: pineapple-onion pork chops
directions: (A substitute for honey-mustard is 1 tbsp Dijon mustard and 1 tbsp honey.)

title: meat loaf (beef)
directions: Place ground beef and bread in mixing bowl. Beat eggs and pour over meat, bread mixture. Add milk and ketchup and mix well. Add in onion and bell pepper. Use enough soy sauce to make mixture moist. Place in loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Stir pasta, cheese, and next 7 ingredients. Spoon into a lightly greased dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake 10 more minutes or until golden brown.

title: neiman-marcus cake ii
directions: Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine.
Mix well and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Combine cream cheese, 3 eggs, powdered sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: butter pecan ice cream(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Toast pecans in margarine for 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Beat egg whites in large mixer bowl until stiff.
Gradually add sugar; set aside.
In another bowl, beat evaporated milk until foamy. Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add balance of ingredients and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into freezer.
Finish filling freezer can with whole milk.
Freeze.

title: lemonade cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine ingredients and beat at low speed until moist.
Beat at highest speed 4 minutes.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Remove.
Pour glaze over cake.

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
With mixer at medium speed, blend Ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Spoon Ricotta mixture over unbaked cake batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out dry.
Cool in pan.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in large pot and cover with water.
Boil until tender. Reserve broth.
Remove chicken and discard bones.
Return chicken to broth. Mix the flour, baking powder, salt and shortening. Blend in milk.
Drop dough by spoonful into the hot liquid.
Cook uncovered for 10 minutes. then cover pot and cook for another 10 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot garlic dill pickles
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pack cucumbers into hot jars with pepper, garlic and dill.
Pour mixture into jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
The mixture will fill about 6 jars.
Place lids and bands on jars.
Place jars in boiling water.
When water returns to boil, begin timing for 10 minutes.
Remove jars; allow to cool.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring to boil the water and vinegar; add cloves of garlic and sprig of dill.
Add 1 tablespoon pickling salt to jars and be sure salt is dissolved.
Add cucumbers.
Pour vinegar mixture over pickles.
Put in boil bath for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Heat fat.
Add green peppers and mushrooms.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes or until soft.
Add flour and stir until blended; slowly add stock and milk. Stir on low heat until smooth and thick.
Add cream, pimento, chicken and season to taste.
Heat thoroughly.
Into slightly beaten egg yolks, stir a little of the hot sauce.
Slowly add the remaining sauce, stirring constantly. Add sherry.
Serve immediately on hot toast.

title: chili casserole
directions: Combine meat, onion and garlic.
Brown in skillet.
Add salt, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Stir in pork and beans.
Pour into casserole dish and top with corn chips and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: six cup salad
directions: Drain fruits well.
Mix ingredients lightly.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Top with maraschino cherry.

title: world's best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt butter or margarine and chocolate together, stirring frequently. With spoon or whisk, beat in sugar and eggs until blended.
Stir in nuts, flour, vanilla and salt.
Evenly spread batter in pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shake pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers and onions in clear jars.
Heat sugar, vinegar, salt and seasonings over low heat until melted, but do not boil. Pour over cucumbers and seal.
After jars cool, place in refrigerator and shake every morning for two weeks.

title: sweet almond trash
directions: Melt almond bark in the microwave.
Mix in the nuts, cereal and pretzels.
Stir until covered.
Pour out on waxed paper and break up when the bark is hard.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put into greased muffin pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Or 1 can beer, 2 cups Bisquick and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using mixer on medium speed. Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, watching carefully after 35 minutes.

title: miss ruth taylor's chicken spaghetti
directions: Add 1 tablespoon salt to boiling chicken.
Cut chicken in squares about 1-inch thick.
In the chicken broth, put chopped celery, bell pepper, mushrooms and olives and cook about 10 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti to broth.
Next, fold in chicken and stir slightly.
Place layer of mixture in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and another layer and repeat until baking dish is full.
Bake until slightly brown at 350°.

title: quick cheese sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine ingredients.
Over low heat, cook and stir until cheese spread melts.
Serve warm over vegetables, baked potatoes, burgers or tortilla chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cajun rice
directions: Follow rice directions on package.
Fry hamburger; drain.
Add sausages and onions.
Cook until done; drain.
Add cooked rice mix.
Put in sprayed casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Place into a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: congealed chicken spread
directions: Chop drained chicken.
Melt chicken soup and cream cheese in pot over low heat.
Stir in gelatin until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate overnight.
Unmold when ready to serve and garnish as desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and bake in a greased casserole pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix dry mustard, salt and pepper with flour and pound into steak.
Melt shortening on medium heat and brown on both sides. Place in a baking dish.
Combine onions, tomatoes, sauce and brown sugar.
Pour over steak and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serves 6 to 8

title: brussel sprout bake
directions: Cook sprouts in 1 cup water till tender.
Drain and cut in half and place in a baking dish.
Spread eggs over sprouts. Sprinkle the cheese over the sprouts and eggs.

title: fancy egg scramble(serves 9)
directions: In a large skillet cook Canadian Bacon and onion in 3 tablespoons of butter.
Add eggs and scramble until set (wet). Fold mushrooms and eggs into Cheese Sauce.
Turn into a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining butter (melted) with bread crumbs and paprika.
Sprinkle atop egg mixture.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.

title: recreation center salsa
directions: Combine everything in one bowl.
Chill overnight.
Makes a lot (about six cups).
Great with chips or on scrambled eggs!

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Beat together sugar, margarine, eggs and baking soda dissolved in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in an 8-inch square pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Beat in order given and put in hot buttered muffin pan.
Bake in hot oven at 400° to 425° for 20 minutes.

title: corn maque chou
directions: Cut kernels off and scrape all juice off of cob.
On low fire, heat oil.
Add onion and bell pepper; saute until tender.
Add corn and tomato.
Season to taste.
Cook on medium-low heat for 1 1/2 hours, being careful not to scorch.
Add very little water, if needed.
When corn is almost cooked, add milk and cook down to desired thickness.

title: sad cake
directions: Stir and bake in long pan at 350° until medium brown.
Cut in squares.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and water.
Boil until mixture forms a thread about 6-inches long or reaches 250° on a candy thermometer.
Add peanuts.
Stir continuously until caramel color.
Remove from stove.
Add butter, salt and soda.
Pour on buttered board to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: egg cheese casserole
directions: Grease a large pan with butter (9 x 13-inch).
Place torn bread and cheese in layers (break bread).
Beat eggs, salt and milk.
Pour over bread.
Prepare overnight and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Put bacon crumbs on top the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken breasts and pound out flat. Place frozen broccoli in centers, adding seasoning of your choice to taste.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish, adding enough orange juice to cover bottom of pan (about 1 to 1 1/2-inches).
Bake for 1 hour, basting with juice.
Serves 4.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: In large sauce pan, melt chocolate and butter.	Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 inch x 13 inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until finger pressed lightly on surface leaves indentation.
Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugars, oil and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in zucchini, pineapple, raisins and nuts until mixed.
Pour into 2 lightly greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake 55 minutes.

title: braised liver and vegetables
directions: Cut liver into 6 serving sized pieces.
Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper; dredge the liver slices.
Brown liver in cooking fat and remove from pan.
Pour off drippings.
Add turnips, carrots and onion to the pan.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and marjoram.
Place liver on top of the vegetables; add the water. Cover tightly and cook slowly for 25 minutes or until done to taste.
Place liver and vegetables on a platter and sprinkle with paprika.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, then flour.
Whip egg whites and fold in last.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: rice dish
directions: Put in 8 x 8-inch dish in order given.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir after 1/2 hour.
Do not double.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Place all ingredients in casserole dish in layers.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: quick-delicious chile
directions: Chop onion; saute in a large boiler in butter until tender. Add ground beef or turkey and brown; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce to low temperature.
Simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: slumgullion
directions: Fry onions until brown; remove from skillet.
Fry ground beef; remove from grease.
Cook noodles until done; drain.
Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Mix well in roasting pan (large). Grate cheese and sprinkle over top.
Place on stove and cook on low until cheese starts to melt.
Serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and let set at least 4 hours.
Can be refrigerated and kept.
Excellent for grilled items, meatballs for hors d'oeuvres or oven baking.

title: junior league tea room eggplant supreme
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Peel and dice eggplant.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain.
Mix ground beef, eggplant, Spanish rice, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Chop pecans.
Chop and mix fruit and raisins, then mix fruit, raisins and pecans.
In a double boiler, melt marshmallows, margarine and milk.
Then take a little of each graham crackers, fruit, raisins, pecans and liquid mixture and mix good.
Continue adding until all ingredients are well mixed.
Put in pans or use graham cracker box covered on inside with waxed paper.
Refrigerate and let set.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13 greased pan for approximately 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine oats, flour, oleo and salt until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 of mixture for topping.
Spread remaining mixture in pan.
Combine rhubarb and Jell-O.
Spread over oats.
Cover with marshmallows.
Cook sugar, water and cornstarch together for 3 minutes.
Pour over rhubarb.
Cover with reserved mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour and spices.
Mix in nuts and raisins.
Add oil, sugar and eggs; add flour mixture, alternating with applesauce. Pour into a large cake pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from the pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan very well.
Dump in fruit.
Dump cake mix on top of fruit.
Thinly slice butter and place all over mix.
Sprinkle spices over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: marinated chicken breast
directions: Arrange chicken in a shallow dish.
Mix marinade ingredients and pour over chicken.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cook on grill for approximately 30 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Cream margarine and flour.
Add pecans and pat out in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: oatmeal sourdough bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 cup of the rolled oats, the dry milk, and the hot water.
Stir well, then let cool to 110°F. Meanwhile, whirl the remaining 1 1/2 cups rolled oats in a blender until reduced to a
flour.

title: monkey bread breakfast treat
directions: Cut biscuits in squares and shake in cinnamon sugar. Place in greased pan. In a saucepan, bring white sugar, brown sugar, butter and nuts to a boil. Pour over biscuits. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Let stand for 5 minutes. Do not slice, pull apart.

title: pecan candy
directions: Mix egg white until stiff.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Mix until foamy.
Add 2 cups of pecan halves.
Mix well.

title: cajun pizza
directions: Make dough according to instructions on box.
Spread into pizza dish and paint with a coat of melted butter.
Season crawfish.
Spread a thin layer of pizza sauce over pizza.
Add crawfish, onion, sausage and jalapeno peppers.
Cover with a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Place in preheated oven at 450° and bake 15 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients together. Sprinkle top with toasted almonds.
Bake in hot oven (400° to 425°) about 20 minutes to 30 minutes until bubbly and brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: "fruit and cheese picks"
directions: Place on toothpicks.
Chill and arrange on tray before serving.

title: sweetened condensed milk(eagle brand)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Equals 1 can sweetened condensed milk.

title: erna's peanut cluster
directions: Melt the peanut butter chips and chocolate chips in microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in potato chips and peanuts.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: zucchini-noodle casserole
directions: While noodles are cooking, saute onions in 2 tablespoons of the butter until soft and transparent.
Add remaining butter.
Cook mushrooms and zucchini for 2 to 3 minutes or until tender-crisp. Stir in herbs, salt and pepper.
Add Ricotta cheese, 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese and the yogurt, combining well.
Gently fold in the noodles.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart oiled baking dish.
Sprinkle with walnuts, if used, and remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: fairy fluff
directions: Cook according to directions on box, until almost done, but not thick.
Add marshmallows.
Stir and let set overnight.
Add 1 can drained crushed pineapple and fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: creamed chicken a la king
directions: Boil cut up chicken in water to cover in a large pot for 35 minutes.
Remove skin and discard.
Refrigerate cooked chicken pieces and put giblets into pot with chicken juice and simmer. Chop celery and onions (hopefully in a food processor).
Sliver green peppers.
Put vegetables into pot.
Add poultry seasoning, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Cook on moderate heat for an hour with the giblets.
Remove giblets with slotted spoon and cool, then dice finely.

title: hamburger gooie
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together.
Cook noodles as directed. Combine soups, sour cream, hamburger and noodles in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes ii
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Heat Velveeta, margarine and milk until melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange sliced bars
directions: Mix together.
Spread out on a well greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.

title: orange roughy filets
directions: Rinse fillets thoroughly in cold water; pat dry with paper towels.
Set aside.
Coat a medium skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saut until tender.

Add celery, carrot, and pepper; cover and cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in thyme, and cook over medium-high heat until all moisture has evaporated; stir in 1 Tbsp. parsley. Spoon an equal amount of mixture on each fillet in shallow casserole dish coated with cooking spray.
Combine mayonnaise, and mustard; spread mixture evenly over fillets, and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sprinkle mozzarella on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish is lightly browned and flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve with rice.

title: posh squash
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place bread crumbs on the top and bake in oven at 300°
for 20 minutes.

title: orzo salad with sesame dressing
directions: Cook orzo in boiling salted water to cover 8 minutes or until tender; drain. Rinse with cold water; drain again. Combine orzo and oil, tossing gently. Spoon half of orzo into a large glass bowl; top with half each of carrot strips, raisins and sunflower kernels. Repeat layers and drizzle 1 cup Sesame Dressing over top. Combine chopped parsley and sliced green onions; sprinkle over salad. Serve with remaining Sesame Dressing. Yield: 10 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just tender.
Chop onion and bell pepper. Mix all together and allow to marinate one hour or longer.
Sauce can be used over salad or chicken can be added and eaten with rice as a casserole.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent roll dough into a cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions on package.
Mix mayo, cream cheese and salad dressing.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables, boiled eggs and cheese as desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Nutmeats are optional.

title: wickers baked beans
directions: Saute diced onion and bacon. Stir in other ingredients.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: pork chops with apricots
directions: Quickly brown chops in butter in saute' pan.
Lightly salt & pepper to taste.
Arrange tightly in glass baking dish.
Cover with apricot puree.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until done. Remove from oven; cover with brown sugar and return to broiler for 5 minutes until glazed.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook them in the cage outside.
Then eat them outside.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over 1/4 cup sugar, the Crisco and the salt.
Cool to lukewarm, then add the yeast, dissolved in 2 tablespoons warm water, and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add the well beaten egg.
Stir in about 4 cups flour.
Mix well, cover and refrigerate. Take out and make into rolls.
If you don't use them each day, punch down daily to get air out.
Let rolls rise about an hour before baking.
Bake for about 10 minutes at 375°, or until done.

title: spiral pasta chicken salad
directions: Cook spiral pasta according to directions.
Add chicken, tomatoes, olives and mushrooms.
Pour your favorite Italian dressing over pasta, meat and vegetables.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours.
