Before serving, mix in Mozzarella cheese. Serve with bread sticks.
(I like the ones from Little Caesars.)

title: italian bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 baking sheets with cooking spray.
Combine Parmesan, oregano, basil and pepper in small bowl; mix well and set aside.
Beat egg white with water; set aside. Unroll dough; separate at perforation.
Cut each strip lengthwise into 2 separate strips, each 1/2-inch thick.
Brush dough with egg white mixture; sprinkle with cheese mixture.
Fold dough strips in half lengthwise; twist each strip to form bread sticks.
Press ends together to seal.
Brush twist with remaining egg white mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese mixture.
Arrange in baking sheets. Bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut the broccoli into small pieces.
Chop onion and grate cheese.
Fry the bacon until crispy.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in separate bowl; mix well.
Pour the dressing on top of broccoli, cheese and onions; mix well.
Crumble bacon on top of salad.

title: express spaghetti sauce
directions: Cooking Meat:

Place the ground beef in a large pan with the olive oil preheated and start cooking until it starts to turn brown, then add the onions, green peppers and Italian seasoning. Lower the temperature and cook slowly until the meat is thoroughly cooked.

title: baked beans, beans, beans
directions: Add a little oil to skillet and cook green pepper and onion. Brown hamburger (add salt, pepper and garlic powder as you cook hamburger).
Mix all other ingredients and beans together in crock-pot.
Add hamburger and cook several hours.
You can also cook in oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs and flour. Stir in 3/4 cup morsels.

title: cracker jacks popcorn
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Boil exactly 5 minutes. Pour over 5 quarts popped popcorn.
Stir good.
Pour into pans and put into 250° oven for 35 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.
When cooked, pour out on waxed paper to cool.
Put into airtight containers and enjoy!

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time. Add baking powder, vanilla, crackers and pecans.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve 1 box each of lemon and lime jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add the pineapple.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
After thoroughly mixing, put in one large mold or several small molds.
Chill.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and butter over low heat; stir constantly.
Add sugar to mixture and blend.
With mixer, blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Beat in 1/2 cup flour, soda and salt.
Then add remaining flour alternating with buttermilk.
Pour into floured pan and bake until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese. Mix thoroughly.
Divide the meat mixture into thirds.
Pat one third in bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover with half of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with the meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine undiluted soup with all ingredients, except cheese. Mix well. Put into casserole dish and spread cheese over top. Place in oven at 350° until warm through and cheese is melted.

title: venison meatballs(dedicated to my husband ronnie)
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Au Jus mix.
Roll into meatballs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: red snapper in wine sauce
directions: Place fish in center of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Mix margarine, lemon juice, parsley, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over fish and make tent of foil.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Open foil and add wine; reclose and bake 10 minutes.
Open and allow to bake, uncovered, 10 minutes or until done.
Garnish with parsley and lemon.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Mix all together.
Fold in 12 ounces Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator 3 hours, then serve.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place on buns.
Bake in foil wrapping at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
May be made ahead and frozen in foil wrapper.
No need to thaw, just add 5 minutes to baking time.

title: cinnamon applesauce yogurt muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine remaining ingredients in a larger bowl.
Mix on low speed with electric mixer or by hand until blended.
Add dry ingredients to liquid mixture (batter will be stiff).
Divide batter evenly into nonstick muffin cups or ones sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serve hot or cool.
Makes approximately 20 muffins.
May substitute vanilla low-fat yogurt and omit use of vanilla extract.

title: "fresh fruit sauce" for pancakes
directions: Thicken cornstarch or arrowroot in apple juice concentrate over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Mash in any fresh berries or fruit.
Add cinnamon to taste.
Warm slightly, if desired, but don't cook.
No more sweet, sticky syrup.

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Clean and devein shrimp. Melt butter. Add peas and mushrooms. Saute. Add shrimp and garlic. Cook until shrimp turn pink.
Add spaghetti and toss or serve sauce separately. Place in oven if mixed together. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Toss with warm cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, cool and dice.
Heat 1/4 cup margarine with soup.
Blend sour cream, onion and cheese into soup.
Mix with potatoes.
Place in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Place corn flakes on top before placing in oven.

title: chinese lemon chicken
directions: In medium size bowl, combine 1/2 cup cornstarch, 1/4 cup water and egg yolks; whisk until batter is smooth.
Add chicken breasts, coating each piece thoroughly.

title: no-peek beef casserole
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: tomato lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions, drain and lay flat on foil to cool.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, heat oil. Add onion; cook, stirring frequently until tender.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring to break up tomatoes; set aside.
In a bowl, stir together Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, spinach, egg, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
In bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, spread 3/4 cup tomato mixture.
Spread about 1/2 cup of cheese mixture on each noodle to within one inch of ends, roll up.
Place each roll-up side down in baking dish; top with remaining tomatoes.
Cover and bake 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella and continue baking just until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: melva's corn casserole
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Saute in butter the onion and bell pepper.
Heat oil in 2 casserole dishes. Pour surplus oil in mixture.
Pour mixture in the 2 dishes and bake at 350°
until done.

title: deviled shrimp
directions: Cut each shrimp into thirds.
Combine cream cheese, onion, Tabasco, Durkee, relish and cocktail sauce.
Mix well.
Fold in shrimp.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into a 5-cup fish mold. Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold onto a platter lined with red leaf lettuce.
Serve with crackers.
Watch this disappear!

title: grandma anna's refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients separately and add to mixture, mixing well.
(It's a stiff dough.)
Divide dough in half and roll into logs on top of waxed paper. Repeat with the other half of the dough.
Wrap each log in waxed paper, twisting ends to secure.
Refrigerate overnight. Slice 3/8-inch thick and place on a greased cookie sheet, 3-inches apart.
Bake at 350° until
golden brown. Dough can be stored up to 2 weeks.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Slice about 3/4 inch from top of head of garlic.
Wrap head in foil.
Bake directly on oven rack 45 minutes or until soft.
Cook potatoes in a large pot of water until soft 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain.
Return to pot.
Unwrap roasted garlic. Press uncut ends of garlic cloves to squeeze garlic paste over potatoes.
Add milk, butter and spices.
Mash until blended. Serves 10.

title: maple pralines
directions: Boil sugar, maple syrup and milk together until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add butter and cream of tartar.
Beat until creamy.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Use with 2 to 3 pounds meat; use half pork and half beef.

title: maureen's artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: roasted corn salad
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray baking pan with nonstick spray. Spread corn on pan.
Roast for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine bell pepper, scallions, green onions, cilantro, vinegar, honey, oil, mustard and salt.
Stir in the corn.
Cover and chill.

title: meal-in-a-skillet(serves 4)
directions: Brown 6 hamburger patties in a large iron skillet.
Slice raw carrots over hamburgers.
Slice onion over carrots..
Slice potatoes over onion.
Season to taste.
Add water and cover.
Cook at low to medium heat.
Takes 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on the amount being cooked.
Check.
Add water, if needed.
Lift with a spatula to prevent sticking.
Add salad or pickles for a meal.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter casserole dish.
Lay 1/3 of tomatoes on bottom.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 1/4 cup cheese.
Repeat with remaining tomatoes.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and dot with butter.
Bake covered 40 to 60 minutes.

title: chilled strawberry soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine the apple juice, 3/4 cup water, sugar, cinnamon and cloves; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat; cool.
Place strawberries and remaining water in a blender or food processor; cover and process until smooth.
Pour into a large bowl.
Add apple juice mixture, yogurt and food coloring if desired.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled. Garnish with additional strawberries if desired.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Cut dried beef into pieces.
Add sour cream, mayo, dash of Worcestershire sauce and dash of Bon Appetit.
If unable to find Bon Appetit, you may use any other herb seasoning.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Best if made the day before it is served. Hollow out round Italian bread.
Cut the center into cubes.
Place dip into center of bread.
Circle cubes around the bread.

title: bernadine's cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Dice chives, pastrami and beef in food processor.
Add chives and meat to cream cheese.
Shape into a ball.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: turkey with ginger salsa
directions: For marinade:
Combine vinegar, sherry, soy sauce, ginger root, garlic and red pepper.
Set 2 tablespoons mixture aside. Pour remaining marinade into a plastic bag.
Close bag; refrigerate 1 hour, turning once.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine peanut butter, softened butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar; beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla extract.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; blend into peanut butter mixture.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle real chocolate morsels over surface.
Place in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; run knife through to marbleize. Return to oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: turkey burger supper
directions: In medium bowl, mix ground turkey, salt, horseradish, apple, onion and 1 tablespoon of the parsley flakes.
Shape into 4 (1-inch) thick patties.
Spray broiling rack with nonstick cooking fat; place patties on rack.
With broiling pan closest to source of heat, broil patties 4 minutes; turn them over and broil 5 to 6 more minutes or until cooked through.
Cut pita bread in quarters; brush with corn oil and sprinkle with rest of parsley.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve with burgers and cole slaw.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Blend thoroughly; press half the mixture firmly in even layers to bottom and sides of a well buttered pie pan.
Save remaining crumbs for topping of Custard Pie.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook ground meat with bell pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add seasoning; let simmer.
Add tomatoes.
Drain corn.
Add corn and beans.
Layer mixture with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: instant fruit punch
directions: Mix well and chill.
When ready to serve, add 4 quarts ginger ale.
Will serve around 60 (5 ounce) cups.

title: slow cooker honey glazed ham
directions: Place ham and soda into slow cooking pot.
Cover and cook at setting #3 for 6 to 8 hours or #5 setting for 3 to 4 hours.

title: simple chicken
directions: Brown chicken, skinned if desired, in oil in skillet.
Reduce heat and pour pizza sauce over.
Cover and simmer about 1 to 1 1/2 hours until chicken is tender.
An alternative is to put browned chicken in a baking pan, pour sauce over, cover and bake at 325° for about 2 hours.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper in a small amount of oil. Add other ingredients all together.
Cook in a crock-pot for 4 hours.
Very good with cheese and crackers.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Brown onions in margarine in skillet.
Add flour and milk; stir until thick.
Stir in cheese and mix in broccoli.
Stir in eggs and pour into casserole dish.
Top with fine bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Cauliflower works too!

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, then crumbs, reserving 1/2 cup for garnish.
Pat crumbs firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: portuguese green beans
directions: Saute bacon 5 minutes; drain.
Add all other ingredients in a pot.
Simmer until done (45 minutes).

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 1 quart of water.
Cool and add fruit juices.
Add ginger ale before serving.
Makes one gallon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Cool and break into small pieces. Put into casserole dish.
Mix together the soups and 3 soup cans of water or broth from cooked chicken.
Pour over chicken.
Put stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until it looks dry enough.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Cut ice cream into 4 equal pieces.
Form ice cream into round balls with your hands.
Mix crushed cereal and cinnamon.
Roll each ice cream ball into cereal mixture and freeze overnight until hard.

title: mango bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes in pans and then finish cooling on a rack.

title: chili meat burritos
directions: Cut meat into 1 x 1/4-inch strips.
Coat with flour.
Brown in cooking oil.
Cut pepper and onion in thin strips and add to meat. Add pepper, onion, tomato sauce, chili powder and salt.
Add water and hot sauce.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Serve in warm tortillas.

title: delicious chicken wings
directions: Mix eggs and soy sauce; add remaining ingredients.
Chop wing tips off; split into 2 pieces.
Soak wings overnight.
Deep fry.

title: beer muffins
directions: Grease bottoms of muffin tins.
Mix all ingredients together, beating vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fill cups 2/3 full and bake 15 minutes.

title: cheese chilies cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a greased skillet or casserole dish for 40 minutes at 400°.

title: cream cheese veggie dip
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar and vinegar in medium saucepan. Over low heat, slowly melt cream cheese in pan.
Stir continuously with a whisk.
Continue heating until thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in onion and green pepper.
Chill and serve with veggies.

title: beans
directions: Add ham, wieners or bacon.
If you do not have cream, milk will take its place if you are sure to add cheese.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in crock-pot which has been lightly greased. Cut thin slices of cheese and put on top.
Cook 2 to 3 hours on low.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fruit slush
directions: Heat 3 cups water with 2 cups sugar until sugar is completely dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together 1 cup water, orange juice, pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Pour cooled sugar water over mixture and freeze for 30 to 36 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in 2 graham cracker crusts and cool.
Makes 2 pies.

title: another barbecue sauce
directions: Boil vinegar (hard boil about 1 hour).
Mix all ingredients and hard boil another hour.

title: pineapple lemonade punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, sugar, pink lemonade and water in a bowl. Scoop in strawberry ice cream. Add ginger ale.
Mix well.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Butter and flour an 8 inch tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy;
separate the yolks from the whites, setting the whites aside.
Beat in the egg yolks one at a time, then add the vanilla.
Sift the flour, salt and baking soda together and fold them into the butter mixture alternately with the sour cream. Beat the egg whites until they form stiff peaks and fold into the batter.
Fold in seeds.
Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake in the center of a 350° oven until top is brown and firm and a toothpick comes out clean.
Baking will take approximately 40-45 minutes.
Make a glaze by blending together the the lemon peel, sugar and lemon juice.
Spoon over the cake and let set to dry.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix together as directed on package.
Add corn and beaten eggs.
Cook ground chuck and onion together and drain.
Add to corn bread mixture.
Grease casserole dish; pour half of the mixture into the casserole. Add half of the shredded cheese. Spread remaining mix on top of cheese.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: blackberry brandy slush
directions: Boil water and sugar until clear.
Remove from heat and cool. Add grape juice, lemonade and brandy; mix well and freeze.
To serve, mix equal parts of slush and 7-Up.

title: surprise apple pie
directions: Fill pie shell with sliced apples.
Sprinkle lemon juice, cinnamon and sugar over apples.
Mix brown sugar and flour; cut in Crisco and butter (fine as meal).
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 1 hour. Watch; may take less time.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown meat lightly and drain off excess fat.
Add celery and onion; continue cooking until slightly transparent.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except noodles, and place in a baking dish. Bake, uncovered at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Cover with noodles and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: cheese chili
directions: Spread grated cheese on bottom of pie plate.
Spread peppers over cheese.
Mix eggs and milk together and spread over cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers. (Town House brand seems best).

title: crescent s'more bars
directions: Separate crescent dough into two long rectangles.
Place on ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, sealing perforations.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon evenly over dough.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 3 or 4 dozen bars.

title: apple streusel bread
directions: Thaw dough according to package directions.
Divide dough in half; let rest 10 minutes.
On floured surface, roll each dough half into an 8-inch square.
Spread each with half the softened butter.
Arrange half the apples and nuts down the center of each dough square.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.

title: strawberry delights
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill.
Roll in strawberry shape. Chill thoroughly.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together croutons and chicken broth.
Set aside.
Mix together soups, onions and pimentos.
Add croutons mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Happy eating!

title: hungarian goulash(crock-pot)
directions: Dredge the meat in flour and brown it in the Crock-Pot. Cover with the onion.
Combine the garlic, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika and mustard.
Stir in the water and pour the whole mixture over the meat.
Cook on Low for 8-9 hours. Turn control to High.
Add the 1/4 c. flour to the 1 c. water and mix well.
Stir into the meat mixture.
Cook on High 10-15 minutes, or until slightly thickened.
Serve over noodles or cooked rice.
Serves 5-6.

title: never fail bread
directions: Mix yeast and water; set aside.

Mix next 4 ingredients, then add yeast mixture and whip with a spoon. Mix and cover until it has doubled (1 1/2 hours). Beat down and put in greased loaf pan. Don't cover. Let rise until it comes to top of pan, about 30 minutes. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix
sugar
and
flour.
Add egg and juice, then cheese and pineapple.	Bake
minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top and bake 20 minutes more.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
In separate bowl, combine onion, soup and mayonnaise.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Place mixture in casserole dish.
Add broccoli; mix thoroughly.
Melt butter.
Add bread crumbs; mix well.
Sprinkle over broccoli mixture.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Soak rhubarb in first 3 ingredients for 1/2 hour os so until well coated and saturated (no liquid needed!).
Sprinkle a teaspoon or so of tapioca in bottom crust before adding rhubarb mix.
Dot with a few pats of butter then add top crust with air slits.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for additional 30 to 50 minutes.

title: vicki's brownies
directions: Mix in order given, stirring after each addition.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey chili
directions: Cook turkey until no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, drained kidney beans, tomato sauce, onion, wine, chili powder, parsley flakes, basil, oregano, black pepper, garlic, red pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
(May substitute ground hamburger for turkey.)
Makes 10 servings.

title: crescent delights
directions: Unroll dough for crescent rolls; lay flat on a 15 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Bake as directed on package.
Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables and grated cheese.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add vanilla and poppy seed.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and sour cream.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured layer pans or an angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Frost with powdered sugar and cream cheese icing.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Bake in large Bundt pan at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: trifle-american style
directions: For best effect, use a round glass bowl with straight sides. Slice jelly rolls into three slices each, total of 9 slices. Layer bottom of bowl and one layer around the sides.

title: mom's persimmon cookies
directions: Mix pulp with soda and set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly; add pulp.
Sift all dry ingredients and mix in raisins and nuts.
Add by cupful to liquid mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet if nonstick (grease lightly if other).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cookies will be soft and moist. Cookies freeze well.

title: cornmeal batter fried chicken
directions: Skin chicken if desired.
Rinse and lightly salt chicken.
In saucepan, cover with water; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Drain pot; dry with paper towels.

title: quick choco-mint fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, salt and milk in saucepan and bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil, stirring, for 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate and peppermint extract and stir until the marshmallows and chocolate are melted and blended.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan and cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook and rinse peas and carrots with hot water.
Blend celery soup and chicken broth.
Place cooked chicken and vegetables in 2 quart casserole dish.
Pour soup and broth mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: steamed mussels in white wine
directions: Heat the wine, lemon juice, shallots, pepper, parsley sprigs, bay leaf and thyme in a pot that's big enough to accomodate the mussels when their shells have opened. Bring to a
boil. Add the mussels and cover. Steam until the shells open (5 to 8 minutes), shaking the pan once or twice during cooking.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat eggs, butter and powdered sugar together until light and fluffy.
Put half of mixture into each pie crust.
Lay bananas on top (half in each pie).
Add crushed pineapple on each.
Sprinkle with coconut to taste.
Top with Cool Whip (cover entire top) and garnish with cherries and pecans.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sweet and sour pork(serves 4)
directions: Cut the pork in 1 1/2-inch strips and brown the pieces in bacon drippings.
Drain the pineapple and reserve the juice.
Stir the cornstarch into the water and combine it with the sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and pineapple juice.
Cook this until it is clear and slightly thickened, about 2 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, melted margarine and 2 eggs.
Pack this mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Spread on top of other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over the top.

title: christmas candle salad
directions: Place lettuce leaf on bottom of salad dish, then pineapple ring on lettuce.
Cut banana to shape candle and place inside pineapple ring.
Drop some mayonnaise over top of banana to resemble melted wax.
Top with whole cherry for flame.

title: country-style apple cake
directions: Peel and shred apples.
Batter is made by adding beaten eggs and salad oil to sifted dry ingredients.
Next add vanilla, nuts and raisins to apples.
Fold these into other mixture.
Mixture is poured into a 9 x 13-inch pan that is greased and lightly floured. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cake is left in pan and frosted.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: First wash, stem and slice thickly the tomatoes.
Roll in cornmeal and fry in hot bacon fat until golden and crusty.

title: chocolate loaf cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add other ingredients and beat with mixer on high speed for 3 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Cream sugar and Miracle Whip.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture, then add water in which soda is dissolved.
Add vanilla. Mix well and bake 25 minutes at 350°,
until toothpick clean.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine scalded milk, mashed potatoes, Crisco, sugar and salt. Let stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve dry yeast in lukewarm water. Add eggs and 1 1/2 cups of flour to milk and potato mixture. Stir, then add yeast.
Add 3 1/2 cups of flour.
Knead with wooden spoon.
Put into greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double. Punch down.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all.
Place in oven proof serving dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers, cut a thin slice from stem and remove seeds. Cover with boiling salted water and simmer for 5 minutes; drain. Cook beef and onion in 4 teaspoons fat until brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Combine thoroughly.

title: stone cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and beat well. Add flour with soda and cinnamon alternating with raisin juice. Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in moderate oven until light brown.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Chill fruit cocktail.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
May be eaten with crackers as a snack or used as a light dessert.

title: mexican bean relish or spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with large sesame crackers.

title: home-cooked soup
directions: Cook meat and vegetables in pot.
When almost cooked, add frozen vegetables.
When all cooked, add chickpeas and/or Great Northern beans and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Skim off fat, if necessary.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture and roll on floured board as thin as possible.
Cut in desired shapes.
Sugar crystals may be sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool and store in closed container.

title: hot spicy meat balls
directions: Roll the first 7 ingredients into approximately 1-inch balls; turn in flour.
Brown in oil, then add to remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add red hot pepper and chili powder, if desired.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Melt butter and mix with pecans.
Place in bottom of "Pam" sprayed Bundt pan.
Top with a layer of cake mixture, then put a small layer of cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Make about 3 layers of cake to 2 layers of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. (Check with a toothpick.)

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and puree.
Make sure you get mixed up well.
Yields approximately 1 quart.

title: chicken stuffing bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat 3/4 of milk and the butter.
Mix with stuffing.
Put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, chicken, vegetables and 1 cup cheese and layer over stuffing. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake until melted.
If you use 6 to 8 chicken breasts, add 1/2 to 1 cup milk to the chicken mixture to maintain moistness.

title: pie crust - sweet
directions: Mix and press into 9-inch pan.
Prick with a fork.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Very good for fresh strawberry pie.

title: pineapple sage stuffing
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2-quart casserole.
In small skillet, cook and stir celery and onion in margarine for 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put ingredients in large mixer bowl and mix at medium speed until well blended.
Pam 2 (9-inch) pie plates.
Sprinkle with flour, wheat germ, cracker crumbs or ground nuts (your choice). Pour pumpkin mixture into prepared tins and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: basic crepe
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or mixer and beat well.
Let batter stand for 1 hour for more perfect crepes.
Yield:
26 crepes.
Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 2 g, fat 2 g, calories 50.
One crepe = 1/2 bread starch exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Blend all ingredients until smooth. Divide between 2 pie shells.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: tart lemon pie
directions: Peel or zest colored outer peel, being careful not to get any pith or it will be bitter.
Juice and strain the liquid.
Put eggs, lemon zest and juice and sugar in blender.
Process on high for 3 minutes.
Add butter and process for 30 seconds.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and chill. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Tomato sauce mixture:
Mix 8 oz. can tomato sauce, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup vinegar and 1 tsp. prepared mustard.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix 1 slightly beaten egg, 1/4 cup chopped onion, 1/4 cup crushed crackers, 2 pounds hamburger, 1 1/2 tsp. salt, 1/4 tsp. pepper, 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixture.
Shape meat into oval loaf.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour rest of tomato sauce mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hrs.
Serves 8.

title: baked chimichangas
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and garlic in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except tortillas, egg and margarine.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Blend together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Then mix in milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: quiche me quick
directions: Steam and drain vegetables.
Arrange in pie crusts.
Mix soup and eggs in blender.
Scatter 1/2 cup cheese over vegetables in each pie crust.
Pour soup and egg mix into crusts over vegetables.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top of the mixture and bake in 375° oven until firm, approximately 45 minutes. Serves 8 (or freeze one pie and save until later).

title: gingerbread cupcakes
directions: Line eight 2 1/2-inch muffin cups with paper bake cups; set aside.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, ginger, cinnamon, soda and salt.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together the egg white, molasses, water and oil.
Stir molasses mixture into flour mixture just until blended.

title: chiles rellenos casserole
directions: Beat half and half with eggs and flour until smooth.
Split open chiles, rinse out seeds and drain on paper towels.
Mix cheeses.
Reserve 1/2 cup cheese for topping.
Make alternate layers of remaining cheese, chiles and egg mixture in a deep 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until cooked in center.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with salad and tortilla chips and refried beans.
Good!

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Do not grease pan or dish. Mix rice, soups and water. Pour into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place chicken on top of mixture. Sprinkle with dry onion soup. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients. Then add remaining ingredients except pecans and cherries. Mix well. Stir in pecans and cherries. Pour into 3 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serve cooled or warm with butter.

title: christmas goodies
directions: Mix all together, then add milk.
Roll into balls and then roll in coconut.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Saute beef in butter until brown, then add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, scallions and green pepper.
In square 2-quart casserole, spread 1/2 of spaghetti, then cover with cheese mixture.
Add remainder of spaghetti and pour melted butter over the top.
Spread tomato meat sauce over the top. Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 20 minutes before you intend to bake.
Then, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herb chicken for 2
directions: Mix the bread crumbs, basil, oregano, garlic salt, onion and parsley flakes.
Dip chicken in the melted oleo, then in the bread crumb mixture.
Place in an 8-inch baking dish and bake for 45 minutes, covered with foil or until done, at 375°.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces and put in a 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Layer the rest of the ingredients as they are listed. Combine mayonnaise and sugar; pour over salad.
Top with cheese. Before serving, garnish with more bacon and parsley.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: chicken cacciatore(diabetic recipe)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Saute chicken breasts about 5 minutes or until golden brown on both sides.
Transfer to platter. Add onion, green pepper, celery and garlic to skillet and saute until onion is transparent.
Add Butter Buds, oregano, basil, tomatoes and rosemary.
Simmer, covered, until tomatoes are completely soft, 5 to 10 minutes.
Return chicken breasts to skillet.
Add mushrooms.
Season with pepper.
Simmer, covered, about 20 minutes.
Serve chicken breasts topped with tomato sauce. Serve over rice.
Two ounces equals 2 meat and 1 vegetable exchange.

title: "southern bread pudding"
directions: Beat together 4 eggs and 1/2 cup sugar.
Scald 2 cups milk and 2 tablespoons butter.
Butter 4 slices of bread and cube. Gradually add hot milk to egg and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add bread and mix well.
Mix in raisins, mix all very well, then bake at 300° in buttered baking dish (1 1/2-quart) in pan of hot water for 1 1/2 hours.

title: old-fashioned spicy cookies(family favorite)
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, ginger, cloves, nutmeg and allspice.
Combine water and rum flavoring.
Add soda to molasses. Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add half the dry ingredients, half the water and rum flavoring, then half the molasses, blending well after each addition.
Repeat; chill dough for several hours or overnight.
On well-floured surface, roll 1/4-inch thick and cut with a 3-inch cutter.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet in a moderate oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned; watch carefully so they do not burn.
Let stand a few minutes, then remove.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: mrs. truman's apple dessert
directions: Separate egg; beat white until stiff.
Add yolk and beat.
Add sugar and beat.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to rest.
Add apples and nuts and mix.
Bake in greased pan 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chili dip
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat just until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Serve warm with assorted raw vegetable dippers and toasted French bread slices.
Garnish dip with reserved tomatoes, red pepper and additional green onions, if desired.
Makes 4 cups.

title: milk gravy
directions: Heat bacon oil in skillet.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Let flour brown, then stir in milk.
Cook until thick and smooth.

title: english lemon pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add eggs one at a time.
Mix well.
Then add extracts (and color) and salt.
Sift flour again and add alternately with buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar in a small bowl and add to the above mixture.
Blend well.
Bake in a 9-inch or 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and dusted with flour in a slow oven (325°) for about 1 hour and 5 minutes or until toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Do not overbake!

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: peanut butter broiled frosting
directions: Beat margarine until creamy.
Add brown sugar, peanut butter and milk, beat.
Spread on warm cake layers.
Place 4 inches from broiler unit.
Broil until topping bubbles.
(This happens quickly.)
Great on angel food cake.

title: easy cherry pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pan.

title: fresh lemon pie
directions: In saucepan, mix water and sugar together.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat and add butter, egg yolks, lemon juice from 2 lemons and cornstarch.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix sugar, flour and mustard.
Add raisins, vinegar, water and cranberry juice.
Cook until syrupy.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Boil vegetables and chopped onion according to package directions.
Drain.
Add cheese and mayonnaise.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Melt margarine and add crackers.
Sprinkle this over vegetables and bake 10 minutes or longer.

title: blender-style coleslaw
directions: In a blender, dice cabbage, carrot, onion and green pepper, about a third at a time.
Add water to cover vegetables.
Cover and whirl until vegetables are finely chopped;
drain thoroughly.

title: hawaiian delights
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add ice water when jello begins to thicken.
Whip with egg beaten until fluffy.
Mix pineapple with sour cream and fold into whipped jello.
Pour into mold. Chill until firm.
Before serving, garnish with fresh fruits.

title: wassail punch
directions: Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons of the above mix with very hot (boiling) water and enjoy.

title: extra special sweet potatoes
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, brown sugar, raisins and walnuts in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
The last 10 minutes of baking, top potatoes with marshmallows.
Enjoy.

title: apple relish
directions: Chop the raisins and put them in a porcelain pan.
Add the apples (chopped and unpeeled) and the juice of the oranges.
Chop the peel of the oranges, then put in sugar, vinegar and spices. Boil for half hour.
This relish will keep all winter in unsealed cans.

title: peggy's easy cheese cake
directions: Whip the cream cheese and 1 cup of powdered sugar until creamy.
Add Cool Whip.
Fill the cooled crust with the cheese filling.
Take pie filling and pour over cheese filling.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Whip jello.
Add salt and sugar.
Fold in rest and chill.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth 1 minute in the blender on high or 2 minutes with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: nachos
directions: Place a sheet of wax paper on a 10-inch glass or paper plate. Cover with tortilla chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave at 50% power (Medium) 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes until cheese melts, rotating once or twice.

title: italian dressing
directions: Mix in bowl for 1 minute.

title: soy bread
directions: Soak soy beans in water, 1 to 2 days in refrigerator.
Drain. Boil approximately 9 cups water.
In blender, combine very hot water and soy beans; will make a milky color (the milk will not be as bitter if the water is very hot).
Blend until finely chopped. Recipe calls for 10 cups soy milk/pulp.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and flour until you can't stir anymore.
Flour board and knead until not sticky.
Knead 10 minutes more.
Place in a greased bowl and allow to rise until double (about 1 hour).

title: taco tossed salad
directions: Cook and stir ground beef over medium heat until light brown; drain.
Stir into taco sauce and heat.
Toss lettuce, green pepper, tomato wedges, olives, cheese and chips.
Spoon hot beef mixture and salad dressing over lettuce mixture.
Top with scoops of "lite" sour cream.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: delicious jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and refrigerate until starts to jell.
Add cherry filling, cream cheese and crushed pineapple.
Mix well and spread over jello.
Add chopped nuts (optional).

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased pie pans (8-inch). Bake at 350°
for 40 to 50 minutes.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: potato scones
directions: Steam potatoes until tender.
Peel and dice into 1/4-inch pieces.

title: lemon creme cheese bundt cake
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese. Add in eggs.
Add 1 cup flour and 1 cup sugar (3 times), mixing well each time.
Add flavorings. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: icebox oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
butter,
lard
and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs. Add remaining
ingredients
and make 2 rolls on wax paper and freeze until
hard.
Take
out
of freezer and slice 1/2 inch thick slices
and bake at 350° until done.
If no brown sugar desired, put 1 1/2 cups white sugar.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown meat and onions together until done.
Drain any grease. Add beans
and salsa, heat mixture until warmed through.
Top with cheese, sour cream and black olives (optional).
Use tortilla chips to dip.
May also be used in burritos.

title: j's barbecue sauce
directions: Sauce onion in oil until limp.
Combine ingredients.
Blend before using.

title: sour cream pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle unbaked pie shell with broken pecans.
Mix flour, cinnamon and cloves; blend the mixture to a paste with a little sour cream, then add sour cream.
Stir in eggs, sugar and grated lemon rind.
Pour custard into pecan sprinkled shell.
Put pie into preheated 450° oven.
Immediately reduce temperature to 325° and bake for 40 minutes or until filling is firm.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix with mixer until thoroughly blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken taco pizza
directions: Prepare shell as directed. Saute chicken, peppers, onions and taco seasoning mix in a saute pan or a skillet until vegetables are translucent. Place this mixture on pizza shell. Spread out evenly. Top off with your favorite cheese or cheeses. Bake accordingly.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Slice the strawberries and mix with 1 1/2 packages of glaze. Set aside.
Place one angel food cake cubes in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a medium bowl, combine confectioners sugar and cream cheese with 1/2 package of glaze.
Beat until blended.
Fold topping into cheese mixture. Spread topping mixture on cake cubes. Next, layer with the other angel food cake cubes.
Spread strawberry glaze filling evenly over top. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: lemon-thyme trout
directions: Preheat barbecue or gas grill on high for 10 minutes.
In small mixing bowl, combine margarine, wine, shallots, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Spray two 16 inch long pieces of heavy-duty foil with nonstick cooking spray; arrange a trout half, skin side down, in center of each piece of foil.
Spread each with half of margarine mixture; top with half of the thyme, the lemon slices and pepper.
Enclose fish in foil, folding edges to seal.
Set packets on rack and cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from grill and let stand for 2 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, then vanilla.
Mix oatmeal with boiling water and let set until water is absorbed.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add oatmeal to creamed mixture and then add dry ingredients.
Bake in large loaf pan at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°. Spoon into pan and bake until golden brown.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix the above and form into meatballs.

title: sausage and cheese casserole
directions: Break up, brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard together.
Place the bread cubes in bottom of a 2 to 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese over cubes.
Pour in egg mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until puffed up and golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.
Preparation:
10 minutes.
Cooking:
40 minutes.
Excellent for brunch.

title: perfect chocolate cake
directions: Combine cocoa and water, stirring until smooth. Set aside. Cream the butter, gradually adding sugar. Beating at medium speed with mixer, add eggs one at a time.
Beat in flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Stir in vanilla. Do not overbeat.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: french pastry
directions: Roll vanilla wafers and mix with chopped nuts.
Set aside.

title: champion cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese, sour cream, butter and eggs stand at room temperature for at least one hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first four ingredients over medium heat until the peanuts stop popping.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir baking soda into mixture thoroughly.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet. Cool, then break into pieces.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender in order given.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth and frothy.
Serves 6.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Keep in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons per cup of hot water.
You may want to alter the amounts to suit your own taste.

title: cranberry-cinnamon punch
directions: Combine candies and water in a small saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until candy melts.
Remove from heat. Cool, cover and chill. Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix above and bake in a Bundt pan (use Pam).
Can divide and put in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out in a jelly roll pan; press seams together.
Spread hash browns out on crescent rolls, then spread browned sausage on that.
Add the egg-milk mixture.
Salt and pepper; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and pack in loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Scrub sweet potatoes, cover with boiling salted water, cover pot, and simmer for 30 minutes, or until the potatoes are tender.

title: jogging in a jar
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Drink 2 ounces or more once a day.

title: strawberry-banana pie
directions: Bake a 9-inch or 8-inch pie shell.
After it has cooled, add strawberries, then bananas and top with whipped cream.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly until mixture
reaches soft ball stage.
Add pecans and vanilla. Beat and drop by tablespoons onto buttered wax paper to form patties.

title: carrot cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, cinnamon and sugar together.
Beat eggs well and add oil.
Add to dry mixture and mix well.
Stir in carrots and pecans.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 45 minutes or more).

title: best ever banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare pans.
Mash bananas.
Add sugar and slightly beaten egg.
Add the melted butter.
Add dry ingredients and bake in prepared muffin tins for 20 minutes. Makes 9 large muffins.

title: mother's gingerbread
directions: Mix shortening, molasses and brown sugar.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well and stir in boiling water.
Fold in beaten eggs.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or hot applesauce flavored with cinnamon.
This is the Gingerbread Mother made when I was a child, what precious memories.

title: rummy baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan.
Combine all other ingredients and pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°, basting several times.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Mix together in the top of a double boiler.
Beat with rotary or electric mixer for 1 minute or until well mixed.
Cook over rapidly boiling water, beating constantly, about 4 minutes, or until frosting will stand up in stiff peaks.
Stir frosting up from bottom and sides occasionally with scraper or spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread (about 1 minute).
Makes enough for a 9 x 9 x 2-inch cake or two 8-inch layers.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Beat eggs until thick and light. Beat sugar in gradually. Add lemon juice. Fold in flour, a small amount at a time.
Add hot milk all at once, mixing quickly. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Invert pan 1 hour to cool.

title: toffee
directions: Line pan with foil or wax paper.
Sprinkle half of walnuts on bottom of pan.
Heat sugar and butter in heavy saucepan until mixture turns a medium brown.
Spread hot sugar mixture over nuts, then sprinkle crumbled Hershey bars over mixture; spread to even out with the back of a spoon.
Sprinkle rest of nuts on top, pressing until even.
Cool in refrigerator until firm.
Break into pieces with a meat tenderizer mallet.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix boiling water and Jell-O until dissolved, then add cranberry sauce. Stir until melted. Add all other ingredients. Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Crumble flour, salt and shortening.
Beat egg in cup; add vinegar.
Then add enough cold water to make 1/2 cup.
Pour egg mixture into flour mixture and mix carefully until it forms a ball of pie dough.
This can be mixed in a mixer if you have dough hooks.

title: mousse au chocolat
directions: If not using Grand Marnier, you may add 1/8 teaspoon orange extract.

title: rock cornish game hens en casserole
directions: Place game hens in a casserole dish, breast side up.
Mix together next 3 ingredients and spoon over hens.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting now and then.
Serve with fluffy rice, spooning sauce over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook fresh or frozen broccoli.
Cook onions until tender.
In saucepan, melt half of butter.
Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until bubbling.
Decrease heat. Blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Place vegetables in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce mixture over; mix lightly. Top with American cheese.
Melt remaining butter and toss with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as package label directs.
Drain and then rinse with cold water.
Place in a large bowl.
Add cucumber, green pepper, relish and grated onion; mix well.

title: souper baked chicken
directions: Place salt and peppered chicken in baking dish. Cover with chicken soup. Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 375° until tender (approximately 2 hours).
Remove foil and continue cooking for 10 to 15 minutes. When done, chicken will be very tender and soup will make excellent gravy.

title: cherry-pecan cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and egg; add flour and cream of tartar.
Add cherries and pecans.
Drop by the teaspoonful or roll and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Salt and pepper ground beef.
Spread lightly in casserole dish.
Cover with soup.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese hot sour soup
directions: Slice pork thinly into bite-size pieces.
In 2-quart saucepan cook pork pieces in hot oil until lightly browned.
Drain and set aside.
In same saucepan bring chicken broth to boiling.
Add pork, bamboo shoots and mushrooms.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add vinegar, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Blend together cornstarch and water; stir into soup.
Cook and stir until slightly thick and bubbly.
Stir broth to swirl; pour the egg into center of swirl. Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Garnish with chopped green onions.
Makes 5 servings.

title: ham biscuit
directions: Saute butter, poppy seed, mustard, Worcestershire
and onion (chopped fine).
Remove rolls from pan without taking apart. Slice in half and return the bottom half to pan.
Then layer ingredients in the following order: ham, cheese and onion mixture. Replace top of rolls and cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream(vanilla)
directions: Mix sugar, flavoring, evaporated milk and eggs together.
Pour into freezer bucket.
Fill the rest of bucket up with the homogenized milk and stir.
It is ready to freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, except granola; add it last.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Slightly brown onions in shortening.
Add beans, sugar and catsup. Mix thoroughly, then place the bacon on top of beans. Bake in hot oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender. Drain, mash and add pimiento, onion soup and sour cream. Mix stuffing and melted butter. Line bottom of casserole with this mixture. Reserve some to sprinkle on top. Pour in squash mixture. Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best ever jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add bananas, berries, pineapple and lime juice.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into mold and chill until set. (Leave remaining mixture at room temperature.) Spread firm Jell-O with sour cream.
Spoon rest of Jell-O mix over sour cream and chill until firm.
Serves 12.
Best if made day before use!

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt margarine in medium bowl on High.
Add sugar, cocoa, vanilla and milk; mix well.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes and 10 seconds (no longer).
Remove and add peanut butter; mix well. Pour into greased pan.

title: party size cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine and 1/3 cup sugar and press into a 13 x 18-inch cake pan or two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Cream together cream cheese and 2 cups of sugar.
Beat in eggs and add lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is firm. Mix together sour cream, 4 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Spread on hot cheese cake and leave in oven to cool, oven off and door open.

title: maple nut sundae
directions: Toast walnuts by spreading them in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring frequently until golden brown.
Heat syrup and butter in medium saucepan on low heat until butter is melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Serve over vanilla ice cream.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Cook separately and drain. In casserole dish with butter layer veggies and add 1-1/2 to 2 cans cheddar cheese soup. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherry filling into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add pineapple and spread evenly over the cherries. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of pineapple. Melt margarine and pour over cake mix. Sprinkle coconut and pecans on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot and pour all ingredients over roast. Cook on low all day. It will be moist. It will come right off the bone. Very tasty.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Cut Idaho baking potatoes in half lengthwise.
With the tip of a sharp knife, lightly cross-hatch cut side of potato.
Sprinkle about 1 teaspoon olive oil over each half.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place on microwavable dish and microwave on High for 6 or 7 minutes, rotating once, until cooked through.
Transfer to broiler pan.
Sprinkle again with olive oil.
Sprinkle with about 1 teaspoon Parmesan cheese and broil for about 3 minutes, until cheese is browned.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs 1 at a time. Sift flour and salt. Add alternately with milk. Add flavoring and walnuts. Beat well. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili
directions: Preheat family skillet or 3-quart saucepan over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Brown ground beef, about 5 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper and celery; saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add salt, paprika, chili powder and tomatoes; stir to combine.
Cover.
When steam escapes from cover, reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Add kidney beans; heat until hot, about 4 minutes. Serve with crackers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crabmeat fettucine
directions: Cook fettucine until tender.
In saucepan, melt margarine and add flour.
Add half and half and then stir until thick.
Mix in the cheese and then crab meat.
Toss mixture with fettucine.

title: beef taco bake
directions: In skillet over medium heat, cook beef.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, salsa, milk, tortillas and half the cheese.
Spoon into 2 quart shallow baking dish.
Cover and bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with the rest of the cheese.

title: ramona's crab dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until blended. Add chopped crab and green pepper. Chill in the refrigerator for a couple of hours. Use pretzels or crackers for dipping.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in cold water.
Drain beans. Cover with cold water.
Add onions, garlic, salt and bay leaf. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 3 hours or until beans are tender, adding more water, if necessary.
Add ham last 30 minutes of cooking.
Season with cayenne.
Remove bay leaf and serve over hot rice.

title: no fat muffins
directions: Add the first 9 ingredients with sour milk.
Add raisins, if desired.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned and top is firm to the touch but not cracked.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: mushroom bisque
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and mushrooms; saute until tender.
Add flour, stir constantly until smooth.
Continue cooking for 1 minute.
Combine chicken broth, half and half and nutmeg; gradually add to mushroom mixture, stirring constantly. Stir in remaining ingredients, reduce heat.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring frequently.
Do not boil!
Makes 8 cups.

title: speedy dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in shortening, sugar, salt, milk and eggs.
Blend well.
Gradually add flour (1 cup) and beat well.
Keep the batter smooth and add remaining flour.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Discard outer wilted leaves of cabbage. Cut cabbage into quarters, discard core and coarsely shred. Place cabbage in a saucepan with water, brown sugar, salt and pepper. Cover loosely and simmer for 20-30 minutes or until cabbage is tender and most of liquid has evaporated. Boil down without lid for a few minutes, if necessary. Add vinegar and butter; toss until butter is melted. 8-10 Servings.

title: no bake skillet cookies
directions: Cook sugar, dates and butter on low heat in skillet for 5 minutes.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Cool.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Press into balls.
Roll balls in shredded coconut and then in confectioners sugar.
Enjoy!

title: grandma's lye soap
directions: Add 1 tablespoon of gelatin to all cooked cream pies.
I stir it in with the sugar and add while cooking.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In 8-quart kettle, add 1 1/2 tablespoons of salt to boiling water.
Gradually add spaghetti and cook until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: joshua's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in a large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture. Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and eat.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix altogether in bowl, batter will be kind of lumpy.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown. A 9 x 13-inch pan makes it thick and a sheet cake pan is thinner.

title: "limey" punch
directions: Put softened sherbet in bottom of large punch bowl. Add ginger ale and 7-Up and stir. Be prepared for "seconds" and "thirds", as it is delicious and easy to prepare.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Top with the mixture of the remaining 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: keftehes(greek meatballs)
directions: Mix meat and onion in bowl.
Add all ingredients (except flour and oil) and mix thoroughly.
Dust hands with flour.
Roll small amount of meat into ball (like meatballs).
Fry in oil until browned on all sides (about 12 minutes).
Serve hot.
Makes 25 to 35 meatballs.

title: blender hollandaise
directions: Melt butter until bubbly.
Place remaining ingredients in blender and blend together.
Pour butter in steady stream until all is added.

title: baked beans
directions: Empty beans into bowl.
Crumble 4 slices of the crisp bacon into the beans.
Saute the onion in a little of the bacon drippings until tender and add to the bean mixture with the catsup and mustard.
Pour into baking dish and top with partially cooked bacon.
Bake for 50 minutes or until bacon on top is done.

title: black walnut fudge candy
directions: Cook ingredients to the soft ball stage (or 234°).
When cool, pour into a greased, shallow pan.
When almost cold, cut into squares.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix everything together, except apples.
Mix until crumbly. Pat apples in pan.
Sprinkle crumbled mix over apples.
Melt 1/3 cup margarine. Pour over crumbled mixture.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in the hot water.
Place in a double boiler and add marshmallows.
Stir until nearly dissolved and remove from heat.
Add crushed pineapple, including the juice. Blend together the mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add to lime gelatin mixture.
Chill until slightly set.
Cool the dissolved cherry gelatin, but do not gel.
Pour over lime gelatin mixture. Chill until set.

title: vinegar and oil salad dressing
directions: Combine vinegar and sugar in quart jar.
Shake or stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add oil and garlic.
Shake.
Serve over salad.

title: hush puppies(to be cooked and eaten with fish)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add onion, then milk and last the beaten egg.
Drop by spoonfuls into a deep kettle or deep fryer in which fish is being fried.
Fry to a golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
If a deep kettle is being used, then hush puppies will float when done.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocado pear.
Add all the other ingredients and whip with a fork or in a mixer.
Add enough sour cream to make the right consistency for dipping.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain grease using a paper towel.
Drain corn; place in a casserole dish.
Add onion, bell pepper, Velveeta cheese and Accent.
Add sausage.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°; stir at intervals.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla, zucchini and walnuts and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.
They should be golden brown (cake test with toothpick).
Can make ahead, double and freeze.

title: sugar free cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients with just enough water to make a stiff dough.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together until pudding dissolves. Then add the remaining ingredients.

title: spinach strawberry salad
directions: Clean and tear spinach; clean and half or quarter strawberries.
Set aside to crisp.

title: spinach salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Microwave sugar and vinegar for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Mix in mustard, onion juice, lemon juice, paprika, Worcestershire sauce, poppy seed and oil.

title: marcette
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in 3 tablespoons butter; remove from pan.
Brown round steak.
Mix all together.
Add noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and butter in a large pan.
Stir over heat until it boils, then boil hard for 5 minutes.
Turn off heat and add marshmallow cream and chocolate chips, mixing well.
Salt may be added with chips.
Add pecans last.
Pour into large 1 1/2-inch deep Pyrex dish.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Spread half of this in bottom of large dish.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip; mix until smooth.
Spread 1/2 of this on top of crumbs in pan.
Spread cherries on top of this layer.
Add another layer of creamed mixture.
Spread remaining crumbs on top.
Chill 24 hours, then serve.

title: slaw
directions: Pour over cabbage mixture.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
Shape into ball and roll in crushed walnuts.
Wrap and refrigerate.
Great with Town House crackers.

title: welsh rabbit
directions: Slowly heat butter in medium saucepan.
Add cheese and beer. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese melts. Remove from heat.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Blend the sugar, gelatin and strawberries in saucepan and cook to a rolling boil, stirring constantly. Place pan in cold water. Cool until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.

title: malted milk chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream the oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Fold in balls.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
For large cookies, use ice cream scoop. For smaller cookies, use heaping teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes (light brown).
Bake small cookies for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Beat
sugar, egg and shortening until light.
Add milk, flour and baking powder.	Add cherries.
Bake in a greased 8 x 10-inch pan
for
30 minutes at 350°.
Serve, while warm, with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: raisin nibbles
directions: Add water to raisins; boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in soda; cool. Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and spices.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Allow place for cookies to spread.

title: ed's guacamole
directions: Cut avocados in half and remove seeds.
Mash and add rest of ingredients.
Chill for 1/2 hour and serve.
Great with tortilla chips.

title: pizza dogs
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in a skillet.
Add tomato sauce, cheese and seasonings.
Spoon onto buns.
Wrap each in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together Rice Krispies, sugar, peanut butter and melted margarine.
Roll into balls and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Melt candy and dip peanut butter balls into chocolate and place on waxed paper until dry.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and put juice in pan; bring to boil and add marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Add 1 cup boiling water to lemon jello.
Refrigerate; when cool, add marshmallow mixture, pineapple, cream cheese, whipping cream and mayonnaise.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Pour into glass serving bowl; refrigerate.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Add pumpkin, eggs and milk.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out dough (defrosted) on a greased cookie sheet.
Spread until thin as close to edges as possible.
Beat egg and brush half of it over the dough.
Alternate salami, pepperoni and Provolone over bread.
Sprinkle all other ingredients over bread as for a pizza.
Roll like a jelly roll, covering dough with remaining egg after each turn.
Seal ends and place seam side down.
Brush top with egg and sprinkle sesame seed on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, melt butter over medium-low heat.
Stir in the cream, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, Romano cheese, egg yolk, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until a thermometer reads 160° (do not boil).
Drain fettuccine; top with alfredo sauce and remaining Parmesan cheese.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: my grandmother's pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients and cook on hot griddle.
Makes about 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine and add other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rolls
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar in large bowl.
Mix in margarine until flour is crumbly.
Stir yeast in warm water; mix thoroughly, then pour into flour mixture.
Work dough until smooth.
Put ball of dough in large bowl.
Let it set until doubled in size.
Punch down; knead with heel of hand.
Let it rise a second time to double in size, then make into rolls.
Let rise to top of pan. Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, then beat on high speed.
Bake until a wooden pick in center comes our clean.
(Rectangular pan, 40 to 45 minutes; layer pans, 30 to 35 minutes).

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Stir in cheese. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 3 cups.
Keeps well in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.

title: lemon lust dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts together.
Press into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Add hot water to jello and sugar.
Stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Cut the cream cheese into small pieces and stir into hot mixture until blended until not visible.
Add to mixture one 13 oz.
can crushed pineapple - juice and all.
Add 1 can mandarin oranges - juice and all. Beat a few minutes.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar, butter, and eggs together.
Sift flour, baking powder, and salt; add alternately with the milk to the first mixture.
Pour in berries and spread batter in well greased, floured pan (13 x 9 inch).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite sized pieces.
Add bacon, cheese, mushrooms and onion.
Mix mayo, vinegar and sugar.
Add this dressing to salad and mix thoroughly.
Chill before serving.

title: fruit punch
directions: *All of these are frozen cans.

title: mamma's tea cakes(aunt lizzie knight's tea cakes)
directions: Put flour in very
large
mixing
bowl.
Make a hole in flour. Put in
ingredients.
With
your
hand work flour from all sides of pan
into other ingredients until dough is formed and hard enough to
pinch
off
and press into cookies.
Dough can be rolled and	cut
with
cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at
for
10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all and put in casserole dish.
Put pepper on top and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: squash dressing
directions: Salt, pepper and sage to taste.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° until done or golden brown.

title: tomato, onion and cucumber salad
directions: Dress tomatoes, onions and cucumber with olive oil, red wine vinegar, salt and pepper. Let stand 20 minutes. Serve.

title: cottage cheese
directions: Heat milk until lukewarm (90° to 100°).
Set in a warm place and stir in buttermilk.
Let stand until curds form, probably one to two days.

title: date balls
directions: Mix dates, sugar, egg and butter.
Cook on low heat, 7 to 10 minutes, until thickened.
Remove from heat; add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Let cool just enough to make into small balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: slow-cooker creamy broccoli chicken
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot; cover with frozen broccoli, soup and milk. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook on low all day 8 to 10 hours or high 4 to 6 hours. Serve over rice.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix well soups and wine in casserole.
Season meat with garlic powder, pepper, whatever you like.
Put in casserole with carrots, potatoes and onions.
Mix.
Cover and bake at 250° for 4 hours. Don't peek.

title: fudge
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large bowl and set aside. Combine the next 4 ingredients in a large pan; boil 6 minutes, stirring often.
Pour at once over the chocolate.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into a buttered pan.

title: gingerbread(100 years old)
directions: Pour mixture into a 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Make the sauce; pour on cake while still warm.

title: chewy granola bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, cream brown sugar, sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add honey, vanilla and egg; mix well.
Gradually blend in flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt at low speed.
By hand, stir in remaining ingredients.
Press firmly in bottom of prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until center appears set. Cool; cut into bars.
Wrap in waxed paper for lunch box treats.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Melt oleo and dip breast in oleo and cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Place on cookie sheet, in a Pyrex pan or glass dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: Mix syrup and sugar; bring to a boil.
Do not boil longer than 1 minute.
Take off heat; stir in peanut butter and pour over corn flakes.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper; flatten with a spoon. Nuts may be added to mixture, if desired.
Yields about 40 cookies.

title: luscious strawberry party punch
directions: Combine cran-strawberry drink, ice cream and strawberries in large punch bowl.
Use a whisk to combine until creamy.
Gently stir in soda just before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Chill, peel, chop the potatoes.
Combine with the next 4 ingredients and put into a 9 x 11 in. pan.
Bake about 45 minutes until it begins to brown at 350 to 400 degrees.

title: fruit salad
directions: Take juice from all fruits except mandarin oranges and cherries and mix with pudding and Tang.
Pour over all fruit and mix.
Serve chilled.

title: batter whip rolls
directions: Pour the warm water into a large mixing bowl. Add the yeast. Let stand a few minutes. Stir to dissolve. Add half the flour, the sugar, salt and soft shortening. Add egg. Start the mixer at medium speed or beat by hand until smooth. Stop mixer. Add rest of flour and stir by hand until flour disappears. Scrape batter from sides of bowl. Cover with wax paper. Let rise in warm place for 30 minutes. Drop in greased muffin pan. Let rise to top, about 20 minutes. Bake in hot oven (425°).

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Then drain.
Blend vegetables and pepper. Then mix with all other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry freezer spread
directions: Combine half of crushed strawberries, the lemon juice, pectin and salt in large saucepan.
Bring to full boil; boil hard 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining strawberries.
Add gelatin to water in a small saucepan; let stand 5 minutes. Dissolve gelatin over low heat.
Mix dissolved gelatin and Sugar Twin into strawberry mixture; cool slightly.
Put mixture into freezer containers, leaving 3/4-inch space at top for fruit to expand; cover.
Store in freezer.
To thaw, place containers in fridge for 24 hours before using.
Use within 10 days of thawing.

title: lasagne casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; set aside. Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add cheeses, sour cream, tomato sauce and sauce mix.
Mix altogether with noodles.
Bake approximately 50 minutes at 350°.
Top each serving with Parmesan cheese.

title: steamed white rice
directions: Wash rice until it is clear.
Put water and rice in pot. Bring to boil; stir with fork.
Cover tightly.
Lower heat to lowest level and cook for 15 minutes.
Cut off heat; leave covered for another 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: company chicken(easy)
