directions: Wash chicken. Trim and remove skin. Slice onion. Seed and slice pepper. Place all ingredients in crock-pot and stir to thoroughly coat the chicken. Set pot to high and cook for 4 hours or until chicken is tender. Serve over steamed rice with a crispy salad. Serves 10 to 12.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Whisk first 3 ingredients together.
Add oil; whisk until emulsified.

title: very, very best fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil and cook exactly 6 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients. Beat until firm.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool at room temperature, then store overnight in fridge.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Heat 1/4 cup butter with soup.
Stir in hash browns, sour cream, onions and cheese.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cornflakes on top and dot with 4 tablespoons butter.
Cook 20 minutes longer.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into 1-inch pieces. Cook and drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Mix all ingredients, except cheeses, and place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle top with sharp cheese, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serves 6.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix all in large bowl; let stand in covered bowl in refrigerator for 48 hours.
Stir once a day.
Bake on cookie cooling rack, on cookie sheet at 150° for about 3 hours or until dry to your likeness.
(Can be made with lean beef.)

title: strawberry or peach icebox pie
directions: Cook graham cracker crust as directed.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup of water only.
Mix jello with thawed or partially thawed fruit and partially thawed ice cream.
Stir until mixed.
Can use food coloring to add to color.
Pour into cooled crust and top with whipped cream.
Great and quick!

title: bok choy salad
directions: Chop bok choy.
Place in large bowl.
Chop green onions and add to bok choy.
In a skillet, brown 2 packages of Ramen noodles in margarine and sugar.
(Discard flavor packet.)
Drain noodles on paper towels.
Brown sesame seed and slivered almonds in single layer on cookie sheet in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Add noodles, roasted seeds and almonds to bok choy mixture.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Combine dates, raisins, apples and water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill dough. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Best if kept frozen.
Very moist.

title: never fail caramel icing
directions: Melt oleo or butter.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in 1/4 cup milk until all comes to a boil.
Cool slightly.
Add confectioners sugar and beat until stiff enough to spread.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Brown meat and drain.
Add spices, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Starting with noodles, layer ingredients as follows:
noodles, sauce and grated cheeses.
Make 3 layers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Spread bean dip in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix taco seasoning with cream cheese.
Spread on bean dip.
Shred 1 head of lettuce, place on cream cheese.
Add chopped tomatoes, green onions, black olives or whatever you like.
Add taco cheese.

title: impossible quiche(serves 6)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease pie dish.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion on bottom of dish.
Place remaining ingredients in blender; cover and blend on high speed 1 minute.
Pour into pie dish.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted into center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
You can use any kind of meat you care to.
(Veggies are good.)

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix salad dressing and flour.
Slowly stir in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Add Cheddar cheese.
Stir until melted.
Place potatoes in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Top with salad dressing mixture. Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir together eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.

title: chinese noodle cookies
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients over low heat, stirring until melted.
Add Chinese noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: hot sausage and cheese dip
directions: Saute sausage, beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and heat slowly until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with chips.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with no stick cooking spray.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Beat to a cream mixture; fold in apples, nuts and raisins. Batter will be thick.
Bake 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: anmama's chicken pie
directions: Simmer chicken, onion, celery and 3 bouillon cubes in a pot almost covered with water until chicken is tender.
Cool and remove meat from bone.
Let fat rise on stock, measure out and retain one cup of fat for later use; discard remaining fat.
Slowly heat chicken fat.
Stir in flour.
Add milk a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Add chicken broth and bouillon cubes and continue to stir with a wooden spoon until sauce thickens.
Place chicken pieces in bottom of 9 x 11-inch dish and cover with sauce.
Place sliced hard-boiled eggs on top.
Cover with more sauce.
Place biscuits or pastry on top.
Cook until bubbly, about 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
If using ready made biscuits, add these during the last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Put cherry pie filling in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with cake batter. Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Drizzle melted butter on top. Bake at
350° for 40 minutes.

title: enchiladas de colores
directions: Chop chiles. In a frying pan, heat fat; saute onions. Add tomatoes and chiles; simmer 5 minutes. Fry and soften tortillas; roll small amount of cheese (2 teaspoons) in each tortilla. Place rolled tortillas in baking pan, 6 x 8-inches. Pour chili sauce over the tortillas; sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serves 2.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Soften jello in 1/2 cup water.
Combine other ingredients; blend all together in electric mixer for at least 4 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 9 x 3-inch pan or Bundt pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chewy bread
directions: Mix eggs, flavoring, sugar and margarine.
Then add pecans and flour.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 45 minutes or until light brown at 325°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, oatmeal, onion, salt, pepper, egg and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Put in baking pan.
Mix 1/2 can tomato sauce, prepared mustard, brown sugar, vinegar and water.
Pour over meat. Bake at 350° until done.

title: for the sunday brunch bunch
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Beat eggs; add butter and milk.
Mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased glass baking dish.
Mix all remaining ingredients, except cheese, together and spread over egg mixture.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 250° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries in blender.
Mix with oranges and sugar and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill and then add other ingredients.
Pour into lightly oiled mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, eggs, milk, onions, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Form into 3/4-inch balls, using little pressure. Place on cookie sheets; bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Before serving, place meat balls in heated beef broth.
Yields approximately 90 to 100 meat balls.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook desired amount of potatoes with some salt.
Mash potatoes.
Put your oleo or butter in while mashing.
Pour in some vinegar, a small amount at a time.
Put in diced onion, diced boiled eggs and pickles if desired.
Add desired taste of vinegar in potatoes.

title: tortilla appetizer wedges
directions: In medium bowl, combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix well. Stir in chilies, onions and jalapenos.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread 1 tortilla with about 1/4 cup cream; top with another tortilla.
Continue spreading and stacking tortillas until stack is 4 tortillas high; top with another tortilla that has not been spread.
Make another stack with remaining tortillas.
Wrap tortilla stacks in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Cut each stack into 18 wedges.
Arrange pinwheel fashion around cup of salsa.
Makes 36 servings.

title: spinach cheese bake
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Add remaining ingredients mixing until well blended.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
6 to 8 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add lemon flavoring.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder together.
Add to cream mixture.
Add milk.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Cook cranberries in liquid until they pop, about 2 minutes. Add sugar and cook 1 minute while stirring. Add orange peel and nuts. Chill.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: 1st A.M.:
Grind cranberries and add miniature marshmallows and sugar.
Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Drain mushrooms and save juice.
Cook broccoli in mushroom juice, without any salt added.
Drain broccoli and chop.
Saute onion and garlic in oleo until clear.
Put broccoli, onion, garlic and mushroom soup into a double boiler.
When hot, add cheese, mushroom pieces and almonds.
Season to taste with Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Serve hot in a chafing dish with toast rounds.
Serves 25 to 30.

title: hot mulled wine
directions: In 8-quart saucepan combine sugar, cinnamon, cloves and water. Add orange and lemon slices.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add wine; heat to piping hot, but not boiling; stir occasionally.
Carefully ladle into individual servings of heat-safe punch glasses.

title: coconut and brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add cinnamon, soda, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Beat well, then add flour.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 7 to 9 minutes in 350° oven.

title: bobotie
directions: Beat eggs and milk and pour over mixture just before baking at 350° for 3/4 hour, or until set (not too long).

title: lemon cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add grated lemon rind and salt. Add pineapple. When it starts to thicken, add cheese, whipped cream and lemon juice.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Set broth over low heat, ready to boil when dumplings are ready.
Be sure broth is boiling when adding dumplings, one at a time.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in large baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour over melted butter.
Peel and slice peaches and arrange on top.
If canned or frozen peaches are used, use juice as well. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Cobbler makes its own crust.

title: cranberry apple freeze
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Cover; freeze.
Scoop frozen mixture into drinking cups or serve in dessert dishes.

title: raisin-pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and wet ingredients separately, then together.
Spray muffin tin with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (12 muffins), 8 muffins for 25 minutes.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients (except wafers) together until smooth. Place vanilla wafer in the bottom of a cupcake paper in muffin tin.
Fill with mixture to 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and white chocolate in top of double boiler.
Add peanuts.
Stir well.
Drop on waxed paper on wire racks to cool.
This is very rich so you may want to make small pieces.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown (caramelize) 1 cup sugar in heavy iron skillet over medium heat.
Shake skillet to move the sugar around until it is bubbly and caramel colored.
Combine beaten egg yolks and milk. Combine 1/4 cup sugar and flour and add to milk and eggs.
Pour mixture into skillet with caramelized sugar.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into pie shell. Spread meringue on hot filling, sealing well to edges of the crust. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: almond patties
directions: Blend bread crumbs in blender and mix dry ingredients well. Blend water, oil and celery in blender and add to dry ingredients. Let sit 5 to 10 minutes and fry.

title: preacher cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Cookies will get firm as they cool.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen. Freezes well.

title: mexican chicken dip
directions: Combine sour cream, lime juice, chili powder, jalapeno pepper and garlic.
Stir to combine.
Add rest of ingredients; stir to combine.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: pig's noses
directions: Dissolve Hidden Valley, oil and seasonings.
Pour over crackers in a paper bag and shake for 5 minutes.
Store in dry place.
Eat and enjoy.

title: black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook sausage and onions in large skillet until meat is browned.
Drain and set aside.
Combine cornmeal, flour, salt and soda in large bowl.
In another bowl combine eggs, buttermilk and oil together.
Combine with dry ingredients using a few quick strokes.
Add sausage, onion, drained chilies, corn, cheese and drained peas.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mock boursin cheese
directions: Soften cream cheese with butter until smooth.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Blend in cream.
Form into a ball.
Refrigerate. Can be frozen.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook water and rice until the water is gone.
Add sugar, evaporated milk, margarine, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients.
May be served warm or chilled.

title: wacky cake
directions: In large mixing bowl sift together all dry ingredients. Then make
3 wells, in first well add vinegar, second well add vanilla and third well add cold water.
Mix well with whisk or spoon.
Do not
beat.
Pour into an ungreased 8 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool cake completely before frosting.

title: one pot beef roast and gravy
directions: Place roast in a large baking dish with a cover. Sprinkle roast with dry onion soup mix. In a small bowl, add 1/2 cup of water to soup and pour over roast. Cover and bake roast at a low temperature of 200° or 250° for 3 to 4 hours. Roast will be exceptionally tender. Take roast out of pot and place baking dish on top of stove. Heat the liquid mixture from roast until bubbly.

title: lipton onion dip
directions: Blend all together; chill.
Serve with potato chips.

title: my sister's cucumber dip
directions: Mix a large container of Hood's small curd Cottage Cheese with a sprinkling of Garlic Salt and several chunks of Cucumbers.
Bring out the potato chips and watch it disappear.

title: mari's candy
directions: Melt almond bark.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: tuna delight
directions: Pour contents of these three cans (including liquid) in a saucepan, over medium heat, until steaming warm, stirring occasionally.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate several hours. Serves 8 to 10.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix well and pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine pretzel crumbs and melted butter and firmly press on bottom and up 1-inch on 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in oven 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Beat at medium speed until fluffy all the cream cheese.
Add gradually and beat well 1 1/2 cups sugar, then peanut butter and eggs (one at a time).
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Turn oven off, partially open oven door and leave cheesecake in oven for 30 minutes.

title: marg's snacks
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pour over the rest of the ingredients.
Mix in large pan; divide into two pans.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours, stirring often with a wooden spoon.
Cool and store in tin cans.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Peel and cut length-wise.
Remove yolks.
Place in a bowl and mash.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Spoon mixture into sliced eggs.
Makes 12.

title: big mama's lemonade
directions: Mix together with water to make one gallon.
Use lemon for garnish.
Chill.

title: oven-fried catfish
directions: Pat fish dry with paper towels. In a shallow bowl, combine the next 5 ingredients. In another bowl, beat the egg white and milk. Dip fillets into egg white mixture, then coat with crumb mixture. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Yield: 4 servings.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Fill paper baking cups in muffin pans 2/3 full.

title: potato salad *
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender.
Chill until cool.
Slice (do not peel).
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix gently.
Adjust seasonings to personal taste.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Brown onions, pepper and ground beef.
Do not season.
Add soup, mushrooms and juice, soy sauce, water chestnuts and water. Wash wild rice and drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Place in casserole.
A few cashews may be sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine rice with cheese, sour cream and chiles.
Season with salt.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in butter as for pie crust.
Break egg into cup.
Add milk to make 1 cup.
Beat. Add to floured mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 15 x 10-inch pan, greased and floured.
Cover with pie filling.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and let brown a little.

title: my mother's orange delight
directions: Prepare jello according to instructions on box.
Refrigerate. When jello is partly set add the ice cream and beat well.
Stir in whipped cream and allow to set again.
Put in sherbet glasses to serve and top with whipped cream and nuts.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and ice.
Yield:
Serves 100.

title: carolyn c's salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve as a salad with meats.

title: pasta salad
directions: Add
all ingredients to the cooked spaghetti in a large mixing bowl,
and toss to mix thoroughly.
Chill before serving.	Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix in taco seasoning.
In a large bowl, combine lettuce, tomatoes and olives.
Assemble individual salads using lettuce mixture, meat and remaining condiments as desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain. add onion, celery and green pepper to meat.
Cook noodles as directed.
Layer meat, beans, noodles and cheese and add the soup with small amount of water over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake at 400° in a greased iron skillet for about 30 minutes until done.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Make the first 3 ingredients into crumbs.
Pour the molasses into a 4-cup pitcher or bowl.
Add the boiling water and baking soda; stir gently.
Set aside.

title: dublin potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Drain, peel and cube.
Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Drizzle over still warm potatoes.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, gently fold in cabbage and corned beef, pickle and onion.
Combine mayonnaise, milk and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Pour over salad.
Gently toss.
Serve in cabbage lined bowl.

title: fourteen day pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Cover with brine water that will float an egg.
Let stand ten days.
Pour off brine water on tenth day. Cover with clear water; let stand 24 hours.
Drain clear water off.
Cover with alum water.
Make enough to cover cucumbers. Bring to a boil; let stand 2 hours off stove.
Remove from alum water.
Cover with ice and water until well chilled.

title: triple layer cookie bars(makes 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt Land O Lakes sweet cream butter in oven. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Top evenly with coconut, then Eagle Brand.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt chips with peanut butter.
Spread evenly over hot coconut layer.
Cool 30 minutes.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl combine milk, water and pudding.
Beat well. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped whipping cream.
Layer cream, cookies, bananas.
Top with bananas.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla, ending with flour.
Fold in coconut.
Bake in a 10-inch well greased tube pan or use a Bundt pan and bake remaining batter in a small pan for the family.
Bake 1 hour in a Bundt pan or about 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes in a tube pan.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before turning out.

title: veggie 'n cashew en eggroll
directions: Fry chopped cabbage until cabbage is tender and until water is nearly cooked out.
Season with salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon margarine in 2 cups water.
Saute onions and carrots in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Combine onions, carrots and cashews to cabbage; simmer 15 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Add bean sprouts and simmer 5 minutes.
Season with salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Let mixture cool.
Divide mixture evenly, centered between two corners of the wrapper.
(If the eggroll wrapper were a baseball diamond, center mixture formed like a baseball bat, one end pointing to first base and the other pointing to third.)
Makes 18 to 20 each.
Roll eggroll by folding front corner (home base) over mixture, then fold in the side corners (first and third base), then roll the roll toward the back corner (second base).
Seal the last corner (base-line) with the raw egg white/yolk.
Deep fry in oil until lightly browned.
Serve with rice.

title: cookie crumb crust
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all together.
Press mixture firmly and evenly against bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: breakfast pancake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put butter in black cast-iron skillet and melt in oven at 400°.
Remove skillet from oven, pour in mixture and return to oven.
Bake at 400° for 15 or 20 minutes. Serve with syrup.
Grandkids love these.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Put 1/2 cabbage in large bowl, add a layer of chopped onion and pepper.
Add rest of cabbage, onion and pepper.
Bring to boil the vinegar, oil, sugar and salt.
Pour while hot over cabbage mixture and let stand a couple of days in refrigerator, covered.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain. Add noodles, soups and Cheez Whiz. Prepare frozen mixed vegetables as package directs.
Drain and add to beef mixture. Place in casserole. Combine crumbs, dry salad dressing mix and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 large casseroles. Serves 16.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix
ingredients,
using
only	1/2 can of French fried onion rings
and	pour into baking dish.	Bake in a 350° oven for
30 minutes.
Top
with remaining half can of onion rings and bake 10 more minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and mix with broccoli.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with bread crumbs.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Slice chicken in strips and brown in oil.
Add pepper and onion and cook until tender.
Stir in soup, soy sauce and pineapple tidbits with juice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put almonds on cookie sheet in 350° oven for 3 to 5 minutes to toast. Serve chicken over rice and sprinkle with almonds.

title: ranch rice arcadia
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add crushed garlic or minced garlic.
Add rice and stir to coat thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir gently.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Garlic may be omitted; cream of celery or cream of mushroom soups may be substituted.
You may also add browned hamburger or sausage.
This dish lends itself to substitutions, limited only by your imagination.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix chocolate, sugar, milk, Karo and salt.
Bring to a boil. Take off heat and add butter and vanilla, then beat until right consistency.

title: pull bread(coffee cake)
directions: Place nuts, melted butter and brown sugar in the bottom of a lift out tube pan.
Sprinkle the dry instant pudding on top of nuts and sugar.
Place rolls on top of pudding and follow the baking directions on the package of rolls.
Lift out insert and eat.

title: sweet and sour pickles
directions: Mix and pour over sliced pickles.
Keep in refrigerator; should be ready to eat in 2 to 4 weeks.

title: scallops portuguese
directions: Take fresh scallops, wash well and drain.
Dust with seasoned flour.
Heat oil; add scallops and garlic.
Cook quickly (about 8 minutes), tossing lightly in hot fat.
Just before removing pan from heat, add parsley.
Toss scallops to coat with parsley. Makes 3 servings.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Split long ways; get out seeds and dice. Saute cukes in butter until soft.
Process in food processor.
Add soup, broth and sour cream.
Add dill weed, onion powder and white pepper to taste.
Chill.
Serve with crusty bread or serve cold in mugs for a refreshing appetizer.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and let rise in warm place.
Push down and let rise again.
Shape into patterns (twists, circles, etc.) and put on cookie sheets.
May dip in melted butter prior to putting on baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Mix the lemon jello, cranberry jello and boiling water. Add the pineapple with the juice, cranberry sauce, nuts and celery. Chill overnight. Serve.

title: spinach squares
directions: Defrost spinach day before.
Put over strainer and let drip. Press all moisture out.
Put butter in 9 x 13-inch pan and melt in low oven.
Remove and preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and flour; add milk.
Add salt, baking powder and mix.
Add onion, well drained spinach and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cool before cutting into squares.
Makes 32. Freeze in Ziploc bags.
Serve sizzling hot; bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain and squeeze all water from spinach.
Combine with sour cream and mayo.
Chop water chestnuts and onions fine.
Add soup mix.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Delicious on Triscuits, Sociables and Wheat Thins.

title: strawberry surprise cake
directions: Prepare cake from directions on box. Cook in 10 x 14-inch pan. Cool cake.
Make small box of strawberry Jell-O.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour Jell-O over cake.
Cover cake and chill in refrigerator for 3 hours.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook sausage, scallions, celery, green peppers and minced garlic; drain fat.
Cook rice in chicken stock.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: noodles(make in the food processor)
directions: In the food processor put all ingredients and stir until a ball forms.
Use 1/3 cup flour to dust kneading surface.
Turn dough out and knead until smooth.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes. Divide dough into thirds or fourths and roll out to desired thickness.
Let dry for about one hour and cut.
These freeze very well.

title: milk chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, salt, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Turn into greased pan. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: caramel biscuit ring-a-round
directions: Put sugar, butter and water in a glass microwave container for 2 minutes (level 6).
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Add biscuit quarters into mixture; stir.
Microwave for 5 1/2 minutes.
Dump on plate.

title: no noodles lasagne
directions: To prepare sauce, in a large nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Add veal and garlic and saute until veal loses its pink color.
Stir in remaining ingredients except zucchini and cheeses.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
While sauce is cooking, steam whole zucchini 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 12 x 8-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer sauce, zucchini, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan, beginning and ending with sauce.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from oven. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Makes 8 servings.

title: hoppin john
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice and oil or butter.
Simmer until heated thoroughly.
Cook rice according to package directions, using part of ham hock liquid for part of water.
Add oil or butter.
Combine cooked rice and bean mixture.
Serve hot.

title: spinach salad
directions: Layer in dish.
Add 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 cup yogurt together and layer well.
Pour over vegetables.
Grate Swiss cheese on top.
Sprinkle sliced olives on top.

title: pork chops with chicken rice soup
directions: Cover each side of chops with Gulden's mustard.
Dip chops in flour; brown in frypan.
Add chicken rice soup.
Cook on low heat until chops are tender.
Soup will thicken into gravy.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt shortening and cool.
Let milk come to a boil and cool.
Add yeast to lukewarm milk; add shortening, eggs and salt.
Add flour; stir until smooth and put in refrigerator or make out into rolls.
If you refrigerate, it takes a couple of hours to warm enough to make into rolls or cinnamon rolls.
You can make this into loaves of bread if you desire.

title: ethel's special
directions: Park truck.
Walk into building.
Order a patty melt and hashbrowns all the way with large tea.
Eat like the devil!
(Tip Ethel well.)

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and salt; mix until blended.
Press through a cookie maker onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In large pan, mix Ro-Tel, corn, cream of mushroom, cream of chicken and ground beef.
Bring to a simmer and remove from heat.
In baking dish, crumble Doritos chips in the bottom of dish generously.
Then pour the Ro-Tel mixture over the Doritos.
Top with lots of grated cheese and bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Enjoy!

title: halibut chowder
directions: Simmer all ingredients except halibut, wine and parsley for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add chunks of halibut, wine and parsley.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to 1/2 cup milk.
Stir until smooth and add to chowder to thicken.

title: mandel bread
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and flavoring together.
Mix the flour, baking powder and salt to the first mixture.
Add the almonds and raisins.
Form 3 loaves on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; slice when cool and return to the oven for about 5 minutes to toast both sides. Delicious with coffee.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, salt, butter, water and corn syrup. Cook over medium heat to 250° on candy thermometer or until a few drops form a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour in a thin stream over popcorn, stirring constantly.
Butter your hands and shape into balls on wax paper.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Beat milk and eggs together in a bowl.
Add spaghetti.
Place these in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with spaghetti sauce, then crumble with ground beef that has been cooked.
Sprinkle with onion and garlic salt.
Layer pepperoni; sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: venus cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until gelatin begins to thicken.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water together until a drop cracks in cold water.
Pour over stiff, beaten egg whites, beating with mixer all the time you are pouring syrup.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoon on buttered wax paper.

title: mexicala
directions: Put oil in frypan.
Brown ground beef.
Add onion and pepper. Stir about 2 minutes.
Put mixture in casserole dish. Add all other ingredients.
Stir it up. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Fill 1/2 gallon jar with small cukes.
Sprinkle dill in jar as you fill it.
Add salt, vinegar, onions and spices.
Fill jar with cold water and refrigerate.
Leave a few days, then the jar may be shaken daily until salt is dissolved.
Do not use for a few weeks.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour in a well-greased cookie or jelly roll sheet.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts (optional).
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and turn out on a towel.
Roll up in towel until cool.

title: no-crust apple pie
directions: Mix apples with 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Put mixture in pie plate.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 3/4 cup flour together.
Cut butter into flour and sugar. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Stir
this
into cold
mixture.
Add
cup
chopped walnuts (or more if desired).
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated three bean salad
directions: Drain green beans, wax beans and kidney beans and mix. Combine chopped green peppers, sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt and pepper.
Combine and mix.
Chill overnight.
May also add thin sliced red onion rings.

title: praline holiday pie
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and nuts in a saucepan; heat until butter and sugar are melted. Spread in bottom of pie shell. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes or until bubbly; cool.

Prepare pie filling mix with 2 1/2 cups milk. Measure 1 cup; cover and chill thoroughly. Pour remaining filling into pie shell; chill. Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package; blend 1 1/3 cups into measured pie filling. Spoon into pie shell; chill about 3 hours. Garnish with remaining whipped topping and pecans if desired.

title: maria's baked omelet* * * * * * * *
directions: The following two recipes are from Chef Fritz Rechberger of the Ridenhour Ranch House Inn in Guerneville, California, about whom Sam Price, VAMT Newsletter Editor, has written the following:

title: pinch bread
directions: Mix the brown sugar and pudding together.
Can use a Bundt or an angel food cake pan.
Pinch off one loaf bread.
Pour half of brown sugar and pudding mix over bread.
Pour half of melted oleo over bread.
Repeat again.
Let raise until double.
Bake at 350° for about a half hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
For creamier ice cream, omit 1/2 cup sugar and add 1 small box of instant vanilla pudding.
Add milk to fill mark of ice cream can.
Follow directions for your ice cream freezer.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and garlic in hot fat.
Add tomatoes and seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°. Meanwhile, cook lasagne noodles.
Drain noodles.
In a 13 x 9-inch oblong baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, sauce, grated cheeses and cottage cheese, topping with cottage cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients.
Pour in a greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil; add jello and stir until jello has completely dissolved.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip and buttermilk and mix well.
Add nuts and pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill.
This is especially good with orange jello.

title: baked wild rice
directions: Wash rice thoroughly.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add undiluted consomme and liquid from mushrooms.
Let stand 3 hours.
Set oven at 350°.
Cover casserole and bake 45 minutes, adding a little water if rice becomes too dry.
Heat mushrooms in butter.
Remove rice from oven, lower heat to 300°.
Stir mushrooms and butter into rice.
Return to oven and bake, uncovered, until all liquid is absorbed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raisin oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together thoroughly.
Blend in egg, rind and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt and baking powder.
Sift flour mixture, oatmeal, nuts and raisins into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to cool for a short time before removing from cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, butter, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Spoon into dough tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: You can use candied cherries and pineapple if you like.

title: chinese style chicken breasts
directions: In a bowl, mix the soy sauce, ginger, sesame oil, scallions and chile paste.
Add chicken pieces and toss well to coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for up to 24 hours if you want to.
Heat vegetable oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Transfer chicken to skillet and reserve marinade.
Brown chicken 6 to 7 minutes. Flip and cook another 5 minutes.
Add marinade to skillet.
Raise heat to high.
Once it boils, reduce heat.
Add butter and cook until the mixture makes a smooth sauce and chicken is cooked through.

title: nanny's peach cobbler
directions: Grease 9-inch square pan; line bottom of pan with peaches. Sprinkle peaches with cinnamon and lemon juice.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream the butter; add 3/4 cup sugar and gradually beat until fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Spread this batter over peaches.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 this mixture over graham crackers. Cover with a second layer of crackers.
Pour remaining pudding mixture over this and cover with a third layer of crackers. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Beat together remaining ingredients until smooth.
Spread this frosting over cake. Refrigerate for 24 hours. Cut into squares and serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Chill for 12 hours before serving with little breads or vegetables.

title: fox's cracker snacks
directions: Drizzle oil slowly and evenly over mixed crackers.
Sprinkle Ranch dressing over crackers and mix well.
Combine dill and garlic powder.
Sprinkle over crackers and mix well.
Store in Tupperware.
Let crackers set for 24 hours before eating.
This enhances the flavor.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix cans of soup with skim milk.
In the bottom of a greased casserole dish, spread a layer of vegetables.
Cover with soup mixture and grated cheese.
Continue this procedure with alternating layers of vegetables, soup and cheese.
Finish with the soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: rich's favorite uncooked fondant
directions: Blend all ingredients but syrup; mix in sugar.
Knead until blended.
Divide and add tint with food coloring if desired. Shape into balls.
Yields 1 1/3 pounds.

title: quick easy beef stroganoff
directions: In slow cooker, put round steak that has been cut into bite size pieces. Add mushroom soup and dry onion soup mix. Add just 1/4 can water. Cook at least 8 hours. Serve over egg noodles, cooked according to package.

title: quick and easy chicken marsala
directions: Prepare and bake chicken per Shake 'n Bake package directions. Simmer soup and Marsala wine in saucepan. Add chives and drained mushrooms.
Pour over chicken and bake for 10 more minutes.
Serve with rice and vegetable.
tags: Campbell's golden cream of mushroom soup

title: salmon roll
directions: Combine salmon, cream cheese and liquid smoke or Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Shape into ball or log.
Roll in mixture of pecans and parsley.
Roll up in plastic wrap or wax paper.
Chill to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan or two 9-inch pans.
Bake approximately 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and soda; blend.
Stir in shortening; add sour cream, corn and eggs and mix well.
Add green chilies and cheese and stir.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cajun roux
directions: Variations:
Substitute vegetable oil for lard.
However, the taste of the finished dish will not be as good as one prepared with a lard-based roux.
Substitute another fat, such as rendered duck fat or a combination of duck fat and lard for lard.

title: oriental chicken wings(serves 8)
directions: Cut chicken wings into 2 pieces; trim off outer end.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a large bowl; marinate the wings in the mixture overnight.
Drain wings; place in a covered baking dish. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Remove wings from dish; place on a broiler pan.
Return to the oven and bake for 2 hours at 250°.

title: venison potato sausage
directions: Use your own favorite chili recipe but substitute half-inch cubes of venison for the meat in the chili.
Before putting venison into the chili, simmer it in enough water to cover for about 45 minutes or until tender.
You can use the broth as part of the liquid in the chili.

title: crumb coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together until crumbly.
Save 1 cup for crumb topping.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Also good with salmon patties.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Slice Twinkies lengthwise and lay flat in rectangle Pyrex dish.
Slice bananas and lay on top of Twinkies.
Drain pineapple and lay over bananas.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Spread over the pineapple.
Put whipped topping over the pudding. Sprinkle nuts over top.
Refrigerate.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook the bacon until grease is removed, but not crisp. Combine with the remaining ingredients and pour into a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beets and pineapple
directions: Drain juice from beets and pineapple.
Reserve half of each. Heat beet juice and vinegar in saucepan.
Mix cornstarch with cold pineapple juice.
Add cornstarch mixture to saucepan containing hot liquids.
Stir and heat until mixture thickens.
Add pineapple tidbits and beets.
Simmer until heated through.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: dump cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: Melt water, milk and butter.
Pour over dry ingredients. Mix sugar, yeast, flour and salt with previous mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add more flour to make workable (6 to 8 cups). Knead and let rise.

title: sandwich souffle
directions: Cut crusts off bread and butter both sides.
Place 6 slices in buttered Pyrex dish.
Slice cooked chicken or ham or crab thick and place on bread.
Then cover with 6 slices Old English cheese (do not substitute).
Then cover with remaining 6 slices bread.
Whip eggs, milk and salt together and pour over sandwiches and let stand overnight, covered with foil or waxed paper.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300° and serve immediately with warmed mushroom soup with a little milk added to make right consistency for warm sauce.
Makes 6 large portions or 12 small.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spray muffin tin with nonstick spray well.
Pour about 1 1/2 tablespoons of batter in each section of tin.
Bake in 400° oven 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: texas caviar
directions: In a medium-size bowl, whisk the vinegar with the oil.
Stir in the onion, jalapeno pepper, garlic, salt and black pepper until blended.

title: mom's rotten potatoes
directions: Mix all together in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 12.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together and bake in slightly greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until loaf feels real firm to your touch.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 10-inch pie plate.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine in bowl the milk, flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla pudding, butter and egg.
Beat for two minutes at medium speed.
Spread this mixture into pie pan.
Arrange sliced peaches on top in a circle.

title: chunk chicken and cucumber salad
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients except pita bread, lettuce and tomato.
Toss gently to mix.
Serve in pita pocket with lettuce and tomato.

title: carol's brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in all the other ingredients.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch greased pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scones
directions: Set oven at 425°.
Put flour and salt in bowl.
Add butter; cut into pieces.
Rub butter and flour together with your fingertips until mixture looks like bread crumbs.
Stir in sugar. Press and squeeze the dough together with your hands until a firm ball is formed.
Gently roll out the dough until it is 3/4-inch thick.
Cut out shapes with cookie cutters dipped in flour.
Put Scones on greased cookie sheet and brush with milk.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until risen.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Place onions and uncooked hamburger meat in a large pot and cover with water.
Cook over low heat until onions are tender. Add potatoes, tomatoes, corn and English peas.
Add catsup just before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 gallons.
Serves approximately 100 people.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, butter and brown sugar.
Blend with mixer until particles are fine; stir
in
nuts.
Reserve
cup
for
topping.
Press remainder in ungreased 8-inch pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until
lightly browned.
In same mixer bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend
well.
Spread over partially baked crust. Sprinkle
with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes;
cool. Cut into squares.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan; thin like brownies.
Bake in a 325° oven in Pyrex for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter-kiss cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar and peanut butter; add the vanilla and egg. Beat until well blended. Roll into balls about 1 1/4-inch. Bake on ungreased sheets at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until tops are slightly cracked. Immediately press 1 kiss into the center of each cookie. Cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before placing on rack. Makes 2 dozen.

title: spice cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and bake in tube pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: seigo's scrumptious dip
directions: Cut beef and onions in small pieces.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, beef and green onions together.
Add garlic salt. Season to taste.
Form into ball or put in small dish.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix
cocoa, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add beaten egg yolks, then milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly with wire whisk.
Add
flavoring
and
pour
into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue made from egg whites.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and roll into long roll and chill.
Cut and bake at 350°.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix liquid, egg, crackers and salsa. Flake salmon and add to mixture (discard bone and skin). Coat patties with cornmeal and fry in small amount of oil 7 to 8 minutes each side. Serves 6 to 7.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend well on puree. Tastes better with age.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves and 3 starters.
Store starter at room temperature; do not seal and do not refrigerate.

title: cheese and olive balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and form into a thick log. Cut log into 36 pieces.
Wrap one olive in each portion of dough. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: rocky mountain candy
directions: Melt chocolate in a pan in the oven at 140°.
Meanwhile, mix remaining ingredients together.
After chocolate has melted, pour over mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: praline-apple pie
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, bring butter, brown sugar and whipping cream to a boil. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Whisk in vanilla and powdered sugar until smooth. Pour this praline mixture slowly over pie, spreading to fluted edges. Sprinkle with the toasted pecans.

title: pollo verde casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine meat, sour cream, chilies, sauce, eggs, and soup.
Mix well.
Grease large casserole dish (9x13), or use pan spray.
Layer bottom of dish with tortilla strips, pour half of mixture over strips, and sprinkle with half of the cheeses.
Repeat with tortilla strips, mixture, and top with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° until cheese is hot and bubbly. Let stand about 5 minutes to set before cutting into servings.

title: cherry nut bar
directions: Cream the sugar and butter until smooth. Add vanilla and coconut flavorings and eggs. Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Beat after each addition. Stir in nuts, cherries and chocolate chips.
Turn into well-greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Frost while warm with your favorite powdered sugar frosting.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until ready to serve.

title: baked pork chop and sauerkraut
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in skillet and brown pork chops on both sides.
Spread sauerkraut over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Sprinkle with caraway seeds.
Spread sliced onions on top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour. Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer or until tender.

title: stir-fried golden bronzed chicken
directions: Slice desired number of chicken breasts.
Marinate in small amount of margarine for about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper or may use seasoned salt.
Stir-fry until golden brown, about 5 minutes over hot heat.
Add dashes of Worcestershire sauce or soy or teriyaki sauce.
Can vary to your taste.
Quick, easy and tender.

title: rice chantilly
directions: Combine rice, sour cream, hot pepper sauce and 1/2 cup of grated cheese.
Spoon into a buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Open cans of biscuits and form each separated biscuit into 4 balls.
Combine cinnamon, sugar, brown sugar and nuts in a Baggie.
Place the balls in a greased tube cake pan.
Make sure they are placed evenly, and layer until all the balls are in the pan.
Cut butter into small pieces and scatter evenly on top.
Bake until light brown.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Cut the rings of green pepper and onion into halves.
In a large bowl stir together all the drained beans, green pepper and onion rings.

title: spinach enchiladas
directions: In a quart saucepan, combine stock, peppers, tomatoes, onion and garlic.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; simmer for 15 minutes.
In a cup, combine cornstarch and water; add to pan. Stir until mixture thickens; remove from heat.

title: clam chowder
directions: Peel potatoes; dice into a large pot.
Cover with water and boil until done.
Chop onion and celery.
Pan-fry bacon, onion and celery in a separate pan.
When done, crumble bacon.
Add 3 tablespoons flour or so; cook until thick.
Put celery, onion, bacon and flour mixture in pot with potatoes.
Add evaporated milk and chopped clams with its juice.

title: cocoa cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: etta's nibblets
directions: Soak chicken wrapped in bacon in a mixture of the 3 liquid ingredients for 12 to 24 hours in the refrigerator.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti lasagna
directions: Cook spaghetti by directions on package; drain.
Brown sausage; drain.
Add Ragu sauce, tomatoes and Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Add spaghetti.
Grate all cheeses; keep separate.
Put 1/3 of spaghetti in a 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 of each cheese on spaghetti; repeat 2 more times.
Sprinkle a little more Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°, until bubbly and brown.
Best if made the day before serving.
Store in refrigerator until cold.
Cut into squares.
Reheat for 20 to 25 minutes at 250°; serve hot.

title: sopaipillas(fried bread)
directions: Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Work in lard (with hands) and lukewarm water to make a soft dough.
Chill dough 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Roll out dough on a floured surface to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 3-inch squares or triangles. Deep fry in hot shortening.
Brown on each side and drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
To eat, poke hole open and pour honey or smother with butter or sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the sugar, flour, baking powder and milk and pour over the butter.
Do not stir.
Arrange the fruit over this, then sprinkle over the remaining sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
The mixture forms a delicious crust atop the fruit, that is mouth watering.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat peaches including juice to simmer.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole in 350° oven.
Set aside.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter into casserole with margarine.
Then pour warm peaches into casserole. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Great served warm with ice cream.

title: applesauce(servings:  11 quarts)
directions: Place all ingredients in large stockpot.
Cook until it's cooked down into a nice, smooth sauce.
While hot, put up in sterilized quart jars.
Seal and hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Brown chops and place in medium baking dish.
Cover with other ingredients and pour over cream of mushroom soup.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: fritos and chili
directions: Layer chili and corn chips.
Chili should already be heated. Last layer is shredded cheese.
Melt cheese on top.
Kids love this one too!

title: homemade hot dog sauce
directions: Mix ground beef, onions, tomato juice, chili powder, pepper and salt.
In large pan, cook on high until it starts cooking good. Lower heat.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours.
Do not remove grease; it keeps flavor.
Can be frozen.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour,	sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt in large bowl. Mix well.
Use
a
great
big
spoon
to
mix the whole recipe. Add salad oil and beaten eggs;
mix thoroughly.
Stir in strawberries
and
nuts.
Pour
batter
into 2 greased and floured 9
x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.
Freezes well.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a medium bowl and place additional marshmallows on top, if desired.

title: salmon pasta
directions: Cut up salmon into 1/4-inch pieces.
Peel lemon.
Remove all white pith and chop.
Pit an coarsely chop olives.
Saute the salmon in hot oil.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Add garlic, lemon, olives and capers.
Reduce heat.
Salmon will cook in about 2 minutes.
Make sure it does not overcook.
While fish is cooking, cook pasta al dente.
Drain pasta.
Toss into fish mixture.
Add parsley and toss.
Taste for salt.
Garnish with freshly ground pepper.
Serves 2.

title: soft molasses drop cookies
directions: *For a lighter color and flavor, substitute 1/2 cup cane syrup for the molasses.

title: ground beef and eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water until tender.
Saute onions, celery and peppers in a little margarine.
Mix meat that has been cooked and drained, eggplant and sauteed vegetables together.
Add salt and pepper.
Put in a buttered casserole dish.
Add diced tomatoes and bread crumbs, then sprinkle a few bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until hot through (takes about 20 minutes or longer).

title: chocolate molasses cookies
directions: Mix together the first ten ingredients, then add enough flour (several cups) to drop cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend all ingredients together and form in balls.
Roll in chopped nuts, chopped fresh parsley or crushed cracker crumbs.
Makes 2 or 3 (4 or 5-inch) balls.

title: barbecue round steak
directions: Coat meat in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Brown slowly in butter.
Add rest of ingredients, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add more water, if needed.
Serve with hot noodles or over rice.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Heat 2 inches of water to boil.
Add zucchini.
Cover; heat to boiling.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Cool slightly.
Cut zucchini lengthwise in half.
Spoon out pulp; chop pulp coarsely.
Place zucchini shells, cut sides up, in ungreased rectangular baking dish.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt, seasoning and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer 1/3 of sauce, 1/2 of noodles, 1 cup cottage cheese and 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Add remaining Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Freezes very well.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs together; add sugar, shortening and grated nutmeg. Sift soda and flour together and stir in enough to make a soft dough.
Use the remainder to roll lightly.
Roll thin and cut with small cutter.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix in Cheez Whiz until melted, then add the soups, rice, onion and spices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dutch potatoes
directions: The amount of potatoes and onions is determined by size of casserole used.
Place potato and onion slices in cold water; let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Cover bottom of casserole with bacon slices.
Fill casserole 2/3 full with potato slices.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Fill remainder of casserole with onion slices; sprinkle with salt.
Top with bacon slices.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until set, 30 or 35 minutes.

title: butterscotch grahams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break graham crackers in half and place close together on baking sheet. Combine butter and brown sugar in a 1 quart saucepan; stir over low heat until butter and sugar are melted.
Stir in nuts.

title: smoked salmon log
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine salmon with remaining ingredients, except walnuts and parsley.
Chill.
Shape into log. Roll log in parsley and walnuts.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water for 5 minutes; cool. Cream shortening with sugar and eggs. Add vanilla to raisins (leave water in raisins). Add remaining ingredients. Blend and drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: quick and easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in wine, spaghetti and chicken.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Discard skin and bones from chicken.
Cut into 1-inch pieces. Mix chicken with remaining ingredients, except cheese and onion rings.
Turn into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle onions over all and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 12.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In large saucepan, combine milk, rice, sugar and salt over medium heat.
Heat mixture until tiny bubbles form around edge, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours or until rice is very tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into serving dish.
Cover surface of pudding with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until well chilled, at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: toffee
directions: Mix together in saucepan on medium heat.
Stir in one direction at all times.
Place foil on cookie sheet, shiny side down.
Butter foil; melt one bag chips.
Spread after all are melted on greased foil; let cool 3 minutes.
Place toffee mixture on top of chocolate; let cool 5 minutes.
Melt other bag of chips; spread over mixture.
Cut into pieces; keep refrigerated and eat anytime!

title: sausage souffle
directions: Cook, drain and crumble sausage.
Cube bread (tear or cut). Butter a 3-quart casserole and line bottom with 1/2 bread. Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Add sausage and top with bread, then cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings and pour over casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, let it come to room temperature.
Bake at 325° for at least an hour (until it is set and brown on top).
Very good for a brunch.
Serves 12.

title: sam's easy chicken
directions: Skin the chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Salt and pepper.
Pour undiluted soup over the top of chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.
Remove from oven and cover with onion rings. Return to oven and bake 15 minutes.
Cover with foil for the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: chicken florentine
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook onion and garlic in margarine until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch; mix in broth and basil.
Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens; stir in cheese until melted.
Add chicken, spinach and tomatoes; cover and cook 1 minute or until heated through.
Serve over hot cooked pasta, if desired.

title: mud
directions: Read The Carrot Seed or Jack And The Beanstalk; then prepare some tasty mud!

title: four fruits salad
directions: Drain all fruits.
In a large bowl, mix in 1/2 package of vanilla instant pudding mix.
Refrigerate.

title: raspberry slush
directions: Mix and add enough water for 2 gallons (seventeen 1/4 cup). Freeze for 24 hours. Thaw 1 hour before serving.
Chop up and add Sprite.
One half Sprite and 1/2 slush.
(Use four 2 liters Sprite.)

title: potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes until almost done; dice.
Mix all other ingredients.
Put in a 2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops in fat; place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: homemade pepperoni
directions: Combine all ingredients until blended.
Divide in half.
Shape into a roll, 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in foil. Refrigerate overnight.
Unwrap; bake on broiler pan at 200° for 4 hours.

title: sombrero salad
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add water, green pepper and seasoning mix; simmer 15 minutes or until liquid evaporates, stirring occasionally.
Stir in 1/2 cup process cheese spread.
For each serving, cover chips with lettuce, meat mixture and tomatoes; top with remaining process cheese spread.

title: mocha cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix coffee, water and milk in separate bowl.
Add chocolate syrup, cream and cream cheese.
Put into cookie crust.
Chill overnight or at least 8 hours.

title: beer wieners
directions: Cook slow until tender.
Can use crock-pot or large electrical pot.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put rice in a large mixing bowl and add all other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Cover dish and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Pare and slice apples thin.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt; mix with apples.
Put in a 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan; dot with butter.
Add top crust and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In bottom of 11x14 in. dish, layout individual layer of graham crackers. Should cover the entire bottom of dish.
Combine instant pudding, and milk.
Mix for about 2 minutes.
Stir in cool whip, 1 spoonful at a time.
Mix thoroughly until smooth and creamy/
Pour half of new mixture into dish on the graham crackers and spread evenly.
Place 2nd individual layer of crackers on top of mixture.
Pour rest of mixture on top and spread evenly.
Place 3rd and final layer of crackers on top of the mixture.
Open icing, Peel away tin cover and place in microwave for 25-30 seconds.
Take out of microwave and pour onto 3rd layer of crackers.
Spread evenly.
Place in refrigerator for about 1 hour. Cut and serve.

title: salmon stew
directions: Brown onions.
Drain and debone salmon.
Break salmon apart and mix onions, salmon, eggs, potatoes and water.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Add can of milk and simmer.

title: hot crab meat
directions: Combine and mix ingredients.
Spread into fluted edge pie pan. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in
mixing
bowl.
Mix well. Grease a 6 cup muffin tin.
Drop by tablespoon into tin.
Fill each tin 2/3 full.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes or until done. (Toothpick
will come out clean when a roll is pricked, if done.)

title: broccoli-nut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt according to directions on package; drain.
Add soup, mayonnaise and chopped pecans; mix well.
Add eggs and onion.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: surprise orange cake icing
directions: Mix together and ice cake.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding mix. Add oil, eggs and ginger ale.
Beat 3 to 4 minutes, then add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, using a 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix, alternating with milk, to butter and sugar. Mix all fruit and nuts and work into dough.
Put in greased pan by spoonfuls.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: marble fudge
directions: Cook first 3 to soft ball stage;
divide into 2 pans.
Add cocoa to one, place back on heat and bring to boil.
Cool.
Add vanilla to other, heat to boiling.
Cool.
Beat until creamy. Pour one into buttered pan, then pour other on top and marble, or swirl.

title: donna's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cool. Add all ingredients together.
Add Miracle Whip or mayonnaise to mix well.
Chill at least 6 hours before serving.

title: pork tenderloin salad
directions: Boil pork tenderloin until tender.
Let it stand in the liquid until cool.
Drain and cut into pieces.
Hard-boil eggs; cool. Slice eggs and celery.
Chop pecans, pimentos and pickles.
Slice onion fine.
Mix all ingredients together and mix with your favorite salad dressing.
I usually use a boiled dressing made by Kraft.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients (toss well), then add dressing to taste and sprinkle Salad Supreme.
Toss well.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, syrup, water and salt. Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until mixture boils. When small amount gets hard when dropped in cold water, remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Pour over popped corn and form balls.

title: coffee frappe - party punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Then, pour mixture over 1 quart of ice milk (vanilla) that has been slightly softened in a punch bowl.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: taco pie
directions: Line pan with biscuits; set aside.
Brown hamburger; drain and add taco seasoning, water and tomato sauce.
Heat through thoroughly and pour over biscuits.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then top with cheese and bake 10 more minutes.
Serve topped with shredded lettuce and diced tomato.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 1-quart covered baking dish, layer sliced white potatoes and onions, sliced thin, another layer of white potatoes and onions.
Melt the butter.
Add to the milk, salt and pepper. Pour over layered potatoes and onions.
Microwave on High 30 minutes.
If desired, break up cheese slices and place on top. Microwave 1 minute to melt cheese.

title: corn light bread
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch loaf pan. Mix all ingredients together and pour in pan. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until done in center.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
In separate bowl, sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat both bowls together.
Pour in vanilla, mixing well.
Add carrots, nuts, pineapple and coconut; mix until well blended.

title: cheese-potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes thinly.
Layer in greased 2-quart casserole dish:
half of potato slices, seasonings, grated cheese and soup. Dot with half of butter.
Make another layer of potatoes, seasonings and soup.
Dot with remaining butter.
Fill soup can with milk; pour over top of casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Remove cover; sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: aunt lisbet's pralines
directions: Cook and stir all
ingredients
except
pecans over low heat in a heavy 2-quart
saucepan
until sugar dissolves.
Add pecans, cook and stir to a full all over boil, then lower heat and boil slowly 3 to 5 minutes, stirring often until soft ball stage. Remove from heat, beat by
hand
until candy begins to thicken. Drop by spoonful onto
waxed
paper.
Set
aside
to cool and finish hardening.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop spinach and onions in blender.
Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley, lemon juice and dill seed.
Add salt and pepper.
Combine spinach and mayonnaise mixtures and pour into covered dish.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: yabba-dabba-doo squares
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows. Stir until
melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal.
Cool well. Press firmly into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Store in cool place.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla and beat well.
Fold in blueberries that have been lightly in flour.
Grease muffin pan or use paper cups.
Fill three quarters full.
Sprinkle a little sugar on each muffin.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn and cheese casserole
directions: Mix and pour into well-buttered sugar-coated loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, depending on oven.
Test with a toothpick in center.
Outside will be crunchy and inside moist. Cool 10 minutes, then wrap in plastic wrap to keep moist.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Brown hamburger.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box.
Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan. Simmer. Serve over tortilla chips.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Use 3 teaspoons dry mixture per cup of hot water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and put into greased* mold.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with crackers and strawberry preserves.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart nonstick saucepan, combine onion and garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is translucent.
Add remaining ingredients except water and stir to combine.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over medium heat until vegetables are soft, about 20 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, remove about 1/2 cup vegetables from saucepan and set aside.
In two batches, puree remaining soup in blender.
Return pureed mixture to saucepan and reserved vegetables and heat.
Yield:
2 servings, 2 1/4 vegetable exchange.

title: lime dessert or salad
directions: Mix jello, marshmallows, pineapple and hot water; stir over low heat until jello and marshmallows are dissolved.
Cool.
Fold whipped cream or Cool Whip, etc., and cream cheese together.
Add jello mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving. Makes 8 servings.
Can be made the day before, too.

title: helen's pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter together until smooth. Add cream, white Karo syrup and salt. Blend until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg. Pour into a 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until slightly browned and thickened. Then sprinkle the pecans on top of the pie and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes until knife inserted between edge and middle comes out clean. Serve plain or with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: pineapple-lemon slush
directions: Place undrained pineapple, yogurt and milk in the blender. Cover; blend until smooth. Blend in sugar, then ice cubes until chopped. Serve immediately.

title: lemon lime punch
directions: Mix all ingredients (except sherbet); use sweetened Kool-Aid. Float sherbet ice cream in punch bowl.
Serve.

title: asparagus cheese appetizer
directions: Roll each slice of
bread
flat
with
a
rolling
pin. Spread each slice with about 1 teaspoon of cheese spread.	Put an asparagus tip along one edge and roll up bread with asparagus inside.
Cut
each bread roll into thirds crosswise.
Melt butter in a
small
saucepan
over
moderately high heat.	Dip each bread-asparagus roll in the melted butter and place, seam side down, on
a
baking
sheet.
Cover	and refrigerate for 1 hour. Heat oven to
Bake for 5 minutes.
Turn and bake for 3 minutes
longer
until
crisp
and brown.
Transfer to a platter and serve immediately.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Place in greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked lean pork chops
directions: Lay pork chops in greased casserole dish and top with sliced onion.
Sprinkle lemon juice and brown sugar; add ketchup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Whip together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: nut flake crust
directions: Grind together the nuts and wheat flakes.
Add sugar and stir in the unbeaten egg white.
Mix well; press into 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain thoroughly.
Cook onions in margarine until golden.
Stir in flour and add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Add broccoli and eggs, salt and pepper.
Spread in greased shallow baking dish.
Combine corn flake crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle over broccoli.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.
May be prepared early and refrigerated.
Bring to room temperature before baking.

title: cherry nut bars
directions: Save juice from cherries.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, orange rind and vanilla.
Mix dates with soda and water.
Add to mixture.
Then add flour.
Stir in chopped cherries and nuts. Spread on cookie sheet 15 x 10 x 3/4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Ice while still warm.

title: microwave fresh mushroom soup
directions: Place onion and margarine in 4 cup measure.
Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) until onion is tender, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Mix in flour.
Stir in water, mushrooms, bouillon and white pepper. cover tightly and microwave until boiling, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes. Stir in half and half.
Microwave uncovered until hot, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Put the 2 packages of frozen spinach in colander and run warm, not hot water over it until it has completely thawed out.
Squeeze all the water out of it and place in a bowl.
Mix in the soup mix, sour cream, mayo and chopped water chestnuts.
Mix well and store in refrigerator.
Serve with Hawaiian bread.
Put dip in cut out section of the middle of the bread.
Break off the pieces of the bread and place around the dip.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Water as needed.
Cook until beans are tender.

title: old recipe "osgood pie"
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten yolks of eggs, nuts and raisins; mix well.
Stir in beaten egg whites and pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square baking pan with waxed paper or aluminum foil.
In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine chocolate chips, condensed milk and salt.
Cook over low heat until chips melt. Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread mixture evenly into the lined pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Cut into squares.
Enjoy!!

title: spinach dish
directions: Mix butter and flour; add to beaten eggs.
Fold in cottage cheese, spinach and grated cheese.
Grease an oblong pan (8 x 13-inch).
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: frosted sandwich loaf
