directions: Remove all crusts from loaf; cut bread lengthwise into four equal slices.
Spread one slice with softened butter; cover with the first filling.
Butter the second slice; place, butter side down, over filling.
Butter top of slice; cover with second filling.
Continue in same manner with remaining fillings and bread slices until all are used.
Wrap loaf in waxed paper; cover with damp towel.
Chill three to four hours or until fillings are firm. Just before serving, blend cream cheese with cream and salt until soft enough to spread.
Unwrap loaf; place on serving platter. Frost top and sides with softened cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley; garnish with tomato wedges.
Cut loaf into 1/2-inch thick slices for serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush crackers with melted oleo.
Reserve 1 cup for topping. Line bottom of oblong baking dish with crumbs.
Mix rest of the ingredients and spread on top of crumbs.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie\(makes 2 pies)
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Mix with butter.
Add 4 egg yolks, well beaten, then cream.
Add lemon extract and nutmeg. Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 pie shells at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Cut fresh broccoli into 1-inch pieces.
Bring water to a boil; add 1/2 teaspoon salt and broccoli.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain well.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter until vegetables are tender; drain. Stir together mushroom mixture, broccoli and water chestnuts; set aside.
Combine process cheese soup; cook over low heat, stirring until cheese melts.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Stir in garlic salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: In medium bowl, add all ingredients up to the oil.
Blend in the oil slowly with hand mixer until thoroughly blended.
Then add the pressed garlic.
Blend.
Chill.
Gets better overnight. Serve over boiled, peeled shrimp.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix until dough ball is formed.
Spread in pie pan (9-inch). Bake at 450° for 10 minutes if empty and at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, if filled with fruit.

title: heritage cookies
directions: Grind quick cooking or instant oatmeal in blender until flour consistency; set aside.
Cream butter, eggs, vanilla and sugars until creamy.
Set aside.
Combine all dried ingredients and slowly add them to creamy mixture.
Mixture will become very thick.
Add all chocolate chips, all nuts and grated Hershey bar. Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix together soup and salsa.
Set aside.

title: tofu burritos
directions: Saute garlic with cayenne and onions in oil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in green pepper and continue cooking.
When onions begin to soften, add paprika, cumin, coriander, oregano, corn and tofu and continue to saute.
Preheat oven to 350°.
When vegetables are tender, mix in tomato paste, soy sauce and olives. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Lightly oil a baking pan.
Fill each tortilla and roll up, tucking in ends.
Place in pan.
Top with salsa and cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine the margarine, confectioners sugar, peanut butter and vanilla extract and mix well.
Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in a double boiler over hot water.
Dip the peanut butter balls into the chocolate chip mixture.
Place on wax paper until firm.
Yield:
Depends on the size of balls you make.

title: pearadise bread
directions: Drain pear slices, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Chop pears.
In a bowl, combine pears and reserved syrup with egg and oil.
In large mixing bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cheese and walnuts.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and add the egg mixture all at once.
Stir until the mixture is just moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)

title: pink pickled eggs
directions: Hard cook eggs, plunge in cold water and shell immediately. Put eggs in quart jar.
Combine remaining ingredients; heat, but do not boil.
Pour in jar, cool, then cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut lengthwise as a garnish for cold meats, salad or fish.

title: bran muffin
directions: Soften All-Bran in 1/2 of the milk.
Add shortening, molasses and remaining milk.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in 12-cup muffin tin.

title: pacific fruit punch
directions: Combine juices and ginger ale in punch bowl.
Add sherbet, strawberries and some ice.
Garnish individual glasses with pineapple spears and small umbrellas.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in first column, blending well.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 15 dozen.

title: bonbons(candy)
directions: Mix all ingredients together except paraffin and chocolate chips.
Roll into small balls and chill.
Dip balls into melted chocolate chips and paraffin mixture (melt in double boiler).

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in boiling water; cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.

title: fruit and angel dessert
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces; arrange half of cake pieces in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or baking dish.
Top with half of the undrained pineapple and cherries.
Spread half of Cool Whip over all, then sprinkle 1 cup coconut on top.
Repeat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: quick german potato salad
directions: Cube the boiled potatoes.
Cut the bacon into 1/4-inch strips and cook with the onion until bacon is crisp and onion is tender. Stir in and mix well the cream of celery soup, vinegar and chopped pimento.
Pour this over the potatoes and mix.
Reheat in oven at serving time.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix
flour, salt and baking powder; add sugar and milk. Melt the
butter
in
your
baking dish; pour the batter over butter. Add
favorite fruit on top of your batter, with a lot of
juice. Add
sugar and taste.
When done, crust will be on top.

title: chocolate cherry drop cookies
directions: Blend cake mix, flour, oil, water, egg and almond extract. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until edges of cookies just begin to brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for about 1 minute and then remove to rack to finish cooling.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen, 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pound breasts to 1/4-inch with flat side of meat mallet between waxed paper.
Dip chicken in margarine, roll up, then roll in crumb mix.
Lay single layer in large flat glass pan that's been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 50 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: bar-b-que sauce
directions: Mix together.
Heat and
put on 2 pounds baked ham or other meat for a hot sandwich.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Remove stems from mushrooms and chop fine. Saute stems, onion, bell pepper and sausage over medium heat until crumbled and brown. Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. Stuff and place on baking sheet. Bake for 20 minutes or until tender. Serves 4.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well. Grease cookie sheets.
Heat oven to 350°.
Crush stuffing mix into fine crumbs.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place on prepared cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until set.
Serve on toothpicks. Makes 50 appetizers.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together sugar, salad oil and eggs.
Mix together flour, salt, soda, cereal, bran, buttermilk and raisins.
To sugar mixture add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and bran mixture.
Mix well, adding raisins.
Fill greased muffin tins about 2/3 and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Make about 3 dozen, depending on size.
Batter will keep in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: jeannie's raisin pecan pie
directions: For thicker pie, increase recipe 1 1/2 and cook 1 hour.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put all ingredients, except cheese, in skillet. Cover and cook 1 minute. Uncover and cook until tender, turning with wide spatula. Sprinkle and toss with cheese. Yield: 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 24 muffin cups with baking cup liners.
Combine all ingredients except peanut butter cups.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Fill prepared cups about 2/3 full. Press peanut butter cup down into batter to even with batter. Bake 18 to 20 minutes until it springs back when touched.
If desired, sift with powdered sugar.

title: candy coated nuts
directions: Boil sugar and water in pan on top of stove.
Add peanuts. Reduce heat to medium and continue stirring until water and sugar crystallize on peanuts.
Remove from heat and pour in shallow pan (do not grease).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
About every 10 minutes, stir mixture to keep from burning.
Peanuts will have a pink candy coating as they bake.
Very simple and good for snacks or party.

title: bread pudding
directions: Spread cream cheese on slices of bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Cube bread in small cubes.
Place bread in greased baking dish.
Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and sugar in bowl and beat. Pour mixture over bread and let set 15 minutes to soak.
Place pats of butter on top and place dish in shallow pan of hot water in oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Add very little sugar, about 1 tablespoon to big batch.
Cook 2 hours and put in jars to seal.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef along with the chopped onion and bell pepper until the onion and pepper are tender.

title: sausage pie
directions: Brown sausage and beef with onion.
Drain on paper towel until cool.
Roll out 1/2 crescent rolls to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Beat egg with dash of salt.
Mix with meat mixture, adding grated cheese.
Place in roll crust.
Roll out remaining rolls to top pie. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until evenly browned.

title: one pot tuna dinner
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add egg noodles, tuna, onion soup mix and peas and carrots.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 8 minutes.
Stir in sour cream blended with the flour and heat through, but do not boil.

title: cyclone chili
directions: Heat lard in pot.
Add meat, about 1 pound at a time, removing after each pound is browned.
After all 4 pounds are browned, put onions and garlic in pot and cook until soft.
Return all beef to pot.
Rinse cactus pieces in cold water; drain and add to beef. Also add peppers, green tomatoes, tomato paste, beef stock, coriander, cumin, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 2 1/2 hours.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: potato bake
directions: Chop onion, green pepper and pimentos fine.
Crumble bread; dice cheese.
Mix all these ingredients with hash browns and chop in one stick of margarine.
Turn into buttered baking pan.
Melt other stick of margarine and toss with cornflakes for topping.
Add enough milk to fill casserole about half full.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 20.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until mixed.
Cover, chill.
Makes 3 cups.
Great for vegetable dip.

title: baked bean mix
directions: Drain lima beans, green beans, yellow beans, and kidney beans. Saute onions and celery in butter for 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in a roaster.
Place a few strips of crisp bacon across the top of the bean mixture.
Spread tomato paste over the top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Delicious!

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Knead potatoes with sugar; roll out thin on wax paper.
After it doesn't stick to your hands any longer, spread with peanut butter.
Roll up and refrigerate, then slice.

title: king crab a la helen
directions: Place crab chunks in lightly buttered shallow casserole or skillet.
Sprinkle with sherry and salt.
Pour cream over crab to just cover the bottom of the skillet.
Sprinkle heavily with cheese (shredded).
Heat until cream is bubbly, then run under the broiler to melt and brown the cheese.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Add sherbet when ready to serve.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Top with Post Toasties.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add zucchini, vanilla and nuts.
Put into greased loaf pans (makes 2).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wash day cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, egg and butter and then pat in pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, vanilla, eggs and confectioners sugar; cream well.
Pour over mix in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Saute mushrooms in small amount of butter.
Line shallow buttered casserole dish (10 x 10 x 1 1/2-inches) with defrosted and drained spinach, to which salt, butter and onions have been added.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the grated cheese and arrange mushrooms on top.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease Bundt cake pan good, put in nuts, then arrange frozen rolls.
Mix all dry ingredients together and sprinkle on top of rolls.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Let rise for 8 hours.
Then bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: good pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream Crisco and butter together; add sugar and cream.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Sift flours together twice; add vanilla to milk; add flour and milk a little at a time, starting and ending with flour.
Mix well; pour into pan and bake 1 hour until done; test with toothpick.

title: corn dodgers
directions: To the sifted corn meal and salt, add enough cold water to form a stiff dough.
With the hand first dipped in cold water, form into rolls (dodgers) about 4 inches in length and 1-inch in diameter.
Place on a hot baking pan greased with a little margarine.
Put a small lump of margarine on each dodger and bake in a hot oven (425°) until a rich brown and very crisp.
Margarine on top insures a golden brown crust.
Yields 8 to 10 dodgers.

title: deluxe fajita nachos
directions: In medium skillet, combine chicken, spices and seasonings for fajitas and water.
Blend well. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup warm water.
Empty cake mix in mixing bowl.
Add salad oil and eggs, one at a time, and beat. Add lemon flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: barley casserole
directions: Brown barley in hot skillet with butter.
Cool barley.
Pour onion soup and mushrooms in casserole dish and mix.
Spoon barley into casserole dish and stir.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Roll in small balls and space on a greased cooking sheet.
Put a cloth wrung out in ice water on the bottom of a glass and press cookie to shape.
Bake in moderate oven (350 degrees) about 10 minutes.

title: sunday grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water and salt until done, about 5 minutes.
Add oleo and garlic cheese.
I use 1 cup ordinary cheese, chipped, and garlic powder to suit taste.
Cover off heat and let cheese melt.
I stir it until it melts.
Put in casserole and top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy in large mixer bowl. Blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and orange rinds.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Yield: 2 loaves.

title: crushed pineapple and apricot jello salad
directions: Combine crushed pineapple and sugar in pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and pour into bowl.
Add jello, stirring until thoroughly mixed.
Add buttermilk and pecans.
Save a few for top and fold in Cool Whip.
Use a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
In another bowl, beat eggs. Add oil and vanilla.
Mix this into dry ingredients.
Add nuts last.
Bake at 350°.

title: pheasant with sauce
directions: Coat pheasant with flour seasoned with salt, pepper and paprika.
Heat butter in skillet and brown birds on all sides. Slice garlic and add to meat along with olives, water and Worcestershire; cover tightly.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Turn pheasant; add wine.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes longer or until tender. Serve hot with sauce.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, drain fat.
Add sliced onion.
Season with chili powder, garlic salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, drained and broken up.
Add zucchini and stir (may need additional salt and pepper).
Cover and cook over medium heat until zucchini is tender. Remove from pan with a slotted spoon.
Put in a baking dish.
Cover with cheese and bake until melted (350°).
Great with Salsa Brava hot sauce.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in granulated sugar. Put on top of pie and brown.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in the jackets in salted water until tender, but not falling apart.
When cool enough to handle, peel, slice and layer in a buttered casserole with slivered bell pepper and pimentos.

title: peanut butter fruit dip(sugar-free)
directions: Using electric mixer, beat together all ingredients until fluffy.
Cover and chill.
Serve with assorted fresh fruit. Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 people.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar. Add egg followed by applesauce, mix well. Stir in dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 inch oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 45 - 50 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar on cooled cake or frost with a caramel, cream cheese, or white icing.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well so chocolate is well mixed.
Cook in 9-inch pie shell for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mash sweet potatoes.
Combine potatoes with egg yolks, milk, sugar, melted butter, vanilla, allspice, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into sweet potato mixture.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake for about 40 to 50 minutes.
Pie is done when a knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: cheese and pimiento spread
directions: Grate cheese and chop pimientos.
Blend with other ingredients and heat until smooth, adding a little flour, if needed.

title: cookie bars(fun to eat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Spread chocolate chips and butterscotch chips evenly over crumb mixture.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool; chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: liamite's baked beans
directions: Brown slowly hamburger, bacon and onion.
Add ketchup, salt, brown sugar, vinegar, white sugar and dry mustard.
Mix in kidney beans, drained lima beans and pork and beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can easily be made in crock-pot.
Double or triple if needed.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Cook beef in skillet until brown.
Add potatoes, tomatoes, corn and onion in layers; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover skillet; reduce temperature.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: beer bread
directions: Grease metal loaf pan.
Stir gently.
Leave lumpy.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
If baking in glass baking dish, bake at 350°.

title: dutch breakfast cake
directions: Combine all ingredients to a smooth paste.
Butter loaf pan. Bake at 300° for one hour.

title: old south apple pudding
directions: Combine and beat together applesauce, apple juice, yams, butter, nutmeg and vanilla.
Beat together eggs, baking powder and salt.
Fold into apple mixture.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brownie dessert
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray.
In a 9 x 13 inch cake pan, cut 1 pkg. cookie dough into thin slices and line bottom of pan.

title: coq au vin
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Remove chicken from pan.
Brown sliced onions and mushrooms.
Add soup and stir.
Add wine and water.
Stir thoroughly.
Add thyme, salt and pepper.
Replace chicken in mixture.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes to an hour.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery

title: easy oven-fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken pieces with a damp cloth, cheese, thyme, salt and onion powder.
Dip chicken in buttermilk, then roll in crumb mixture.
Place in lightly greased, shallow baking pan or on a greased cookie sheet and bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour, or until meat next to the bone is no longer pink.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Stir yeast, sugar and milk in a small bowl.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
In a separate medium bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt and shortening.
Blend ingredients together until mixed well.
Pour in liquid and mix together until a large ball is formed.
With small amount of flour on hands, pinch off smaller than golfball size of dough.
Roll in hands until smooth.
Lightly press each ball in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Dab each roll with melted margarine.
Cover and place in a warm area.
Let rise 30 minutes or until rolls rise to top of pan (should take no longer than 45 minutes).
Bake at 400° until until brown.
Easy and delicious!

title: squash souffle
directions: Mix together all ingredients except milk.
Add hot milk. Bake in greased dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cake with pie filling
directions: Spread top with pie filling.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top and cinnamon, if desired.
Blend sour cream, egg and vanilla.
Pour over top and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Place 2 tablespoons butter in each of two 13 x 9-inch pans; heat at 425° until hot.
Combine egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Beat at high speed with electric mixer until thick and lemon colored. Gradually add milk and extract; fold in egg whites.
Dip bread slices into egg mixture; place in hot pans.
Bake at 425° for 10 minute; turn and bake 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Pour into hot greased skillet or greased muffin tins.
Bake	in a 350° to 400° oven until light brown.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, shortening, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 3 tablespoons water together like pie crust.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the rhubarb, 2 cups sugar, egg yolks, evaporated milk, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 4 tablespoons flour; pour over crust.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, then at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients for 1 hour at low boil.
Lower heat.
Add the Velveeta, cornstarch and evaporated milk.
Serve.

title: helen's applesauce raisin bread
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix on low 1 minute.
Blend in raisins and nuts. Blend in applesauce.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and wrap in terrycloth dish towel.
This keeps bread moist.
When cold, wrap in plastic wrap.
Place inside plastic bag to keep fresh.
Freezes well.

title: cheese rings
directions: Grate cheese and blend with butter.
Add flour and mix well. Add salt and pepper.
Run through cookie press, using star shaped press.
Form into rings and bake at 400° for 9 minutes.

title: chicken breasts in mushroom sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange chicken in baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with pepper.
Combine soup and cheese; spoon over chicken to cover all pieces.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water until tender, about 15 minutes. Drain and pour into bowl.
While carrots are cooking, blend remaining ingredients. Pour over warm carrots.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 8.
Goes with almost anything.

title: praline cookies
directions: Place graham crackers close together on cookie sheet (one with sides).
Put sugar and margarine in boiler; bring to a boil and boil only 2 minutes (stir frequently).
Remove from heat; add nuts when bubbling stops.
Stir and pour over crackers, spreading to cover crackers well.
Place in preheated oven.
Do not overcook. Allow to cool a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix
well
the
sugar,
brown sugar, shortening, 1 egg, milk, vanilla
and peanut butter.
Fold in 2 well beaten eggs. Add flour,
baking soda and salt to mixture.
Shape dough into walnut size
balls
and
roll in granulated sugar.
Place on a lightly greased pan and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan, then pour raw rice over bottom of pan. Place raw chicken rice.
Pour mixture of soups and hot water over rice and chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sauerkraut and wiener casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in oven about 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: lemon chicken cutlets
directions: Trim excess fat from chicken.
Place chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; set aside.

title: potatoes topped with cornflakes
directions: Mix half of melted butter with potatoes. Add remaining ingredients except cornflakes. Mix remaining butter with crushed cornflakes; use as topping. Bake 1-1/2 to 2 hours at 350°. Serves 10-12.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Melt butter and dip chicken breasts into butter.
Roll chicken in crushed potato chips and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta with primavera sauce
directions: In large skillet, saute vegies in butter until crisp-tender. Add half and half and black pepper. Cook briefly until slightly reduced. Serve over pasta.

title: chicken mayo
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat the butter; add chicken and brown on both sides.
Remove and sprinkle with salt and pepper (if chicken doesn't give off fat, you have have to add a little more butter).
Arrange chicken in a heavy 4-quart casserole or Dutch oven.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons fat from skillet.
Mix in sauerkraut, onion and apples; place mixture on top of chicken.
Cover tightly and bake in a 325° oven until chicken is tender, about 1 hour.

title: mel's spaghetti
directions: Spray a 3-quart saucepan with nonstick coating.
Add ground turkey or chicken, onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, tomato paste, seasoning, fennel seed, sugar, garlic salt, black pepper and if desired, add ground red pepper into meat mixture.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: orange supreme salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 1 1/4 cups of drained juice (use more pineapple than orange).
Add all of the thawed orange juice.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in fruit.
Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan and chill.

title: muffins and boiled custard
directions: Heat two cups of milk in a large glass bowl in the microwave for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile blend the remaining ingredients in a blender.
Add to hot milk.
Cook in microwave stirring every few minutes until thickened.
Makes 10 servings.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: mama's cauliflower casserole
directions: In saucepan, boil cauliflower in water and salt.
Drain and place in baking dish.
Make sauce in skillet with margarine, milk, and flour.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over cauliflower in baking dish.
Rub toast together over cauliflower with sauce and bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: cathy's cabbage soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large stockpot; bring to a boil over high heat.
Then reduce and simmer 60 to 90 minutes until cabbage is tender and flavors have blended.

title: banana nog
directions: Mash bananas in a bowl.
Add milk, honey and eggs.
Stir quickly until frothy.
Pour into glasses and drink.
Makes 4 nogs.

title: spicy indian hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 4 patties.
Broil or grill 4 inches from heat for about 5 minutes on each side or until as done as desired.
Calories per serving: 213.

title: squash rolls
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix and squash.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth covered board.
Knead 5 times.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients; mix well. Add first 6 ingredients until well blended together.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook and drain the spaghetti; break into quarters.
Saute the onion and celery in margarine.
Add the broth and cream cheese. Stir over low heat until the cream cheese melts.
Add all remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt velma's baked oats
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with a whisk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with a spoon.
Raisins, nuts, etc., can be added.
Bake in a 5 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be doubled.
One-half cup of brown Sugar Twin can be substituted for a diabetic.

title: vanilla sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Bring margarine, oil and water to boil and pour over flour mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Beat in eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, soda and buttermilk.
Pour into a 10 x 15-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cool surprise
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Jello until not grainy.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese. Whip until smooth. Fold in mandarin oranges.

title: baked corn
directions: Thicken sugar, salt, milk and flour over heat.
Beat egg; add to corn.
Pour thickened sauce over corn-egg mixture.
Dot with butter as desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for about 45 minutes or until top begins to brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and mash artichokes.
Add mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and garlic.
Top with paprika.
Bake in ovenproof dish for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: lime gelatin mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cream and mix thoroughly.
Add rest of ingredients one at time.
Mix until evenly combined.
Refrigerate.

title: caramel corn
directions: You will need Pam and a bag.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine ingredients.
Store in tightly covered jar.
Serve as needed, using 1 rounded teaspoonful in a cup.
Add boiling water.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; add to first mixture alternately with water.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Mix together the flour and baking powder.
Cream butter and gelatin.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture. Bake cookies on ungreased baking sheet at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: favorite southern jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in jam and preserves.
Stir together dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk to jam mixture.
Turn into 3 well-greased wax paper lined 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake for 40 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Frost with Maple Frosting; garnish with nuts, if desired.

title: easy cookin'
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Cook noodles.
Mix beans and ground beef together.
Layer alternately in casserole dish: beef, beans mixture, noodles and cheese.
Layer again.
Bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy coffee cake
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water; stir until dissolved.
Warm buttermilk.
Pour into large bowl.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar; let cool.
Stir in yeast, shortening, egg and half of the flour. Beat until smooth, then add more flour until dough begins to clean sides of bowl.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 9 cups of boiling water.
Mix sugar and 4 cups of cold water together.
Add to jello mixture and then add pineapple juice and lemon juice to jello mixture.,
Mix well and freeze.

title: five flavor cake(bundt cake)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening until light and fluffy. Add eggs which have been beaten until lemon colored.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 320° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add glaze, if desired, or cool in pan about 10 minutes before turning out on rack to cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour water over brans; let stand.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in bran mixture, baking powder, soda, salt and buttermilk.
Add flour, mixing lightly.
Fill greased muffin tins 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Batter keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: good brunch casserole
directions: Place broken bread in bottom of buttered casserole. Spread cubed ham and cheese over bread. Pour egg-milk mixture over all and bake 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: fat-free crispy oven potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sliced peeled potato in half length-wise.
Take each half and slice into long strips or wedges, making about 4-5 pieces from each half.
Dip each potato wedge in egg white and then roll in crushed corn flakes.
Place wedges on a baking sheet sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and spray potatoes lightly with butter flavored non-stick cooking spray.
Bake for 35-40 minutes.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and salt.
Blend flour with butter and sugar mixture, a little at a time.
Form balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Place on greased cookie sheet, about an inch apart.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes in 400° oven.
Watch closely as they brown suddenly.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: sour cucumbers salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Pour over cucumbers about 1/2 hour before serving. Salt cucumbers and refrigerate.
Pour off water.

title: fish loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place loaf in an oiled loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until brown and firm.
Yield:
5 servings. Carbohydrate 21 g, protein 30 g, fat 10 g, calories 294.
One serving = 3 1/2 meat low-fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 vegetable exchange.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: *I chop mine in a dicer.

title: easy cheese dip
directions: Brown the sausage and ground round in a large frying pan over medium heat and drain off the grease.
Add the cheese, tomatoes and salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until the cheese has melted and the liquid from the tomatoes has cooked away, about 15 minutes.
If you want to make this dip a bit more elaborate, add a total of 1 cup sauteed onion, green pepper or fresh tomatoes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese with jello well.
Add Cool Whip (30 minutes soft).
Mix well.
Add pineapple and pecans; mix together.

title: 1-2-3 cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in Corning Ware dish.
Mix milk, flour and sugar with melted margarine. Add peaches to mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 325° or until browned.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease 9-inch spring pan (leaving 1-inch at the top). Dust with graham cracker crumbs.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: strawberry spinach salad with lemon dressing
directions: Rinse and drain the spinach. Arrange on serving plates and top with strawberries and walnuts. Serve with lemon dressing and walnuts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, cinnamon, salt, vanilla, baking powder and baking soda, mixing well.
Alternately add flour and zucchini. Blend well.
Fold in optional chopped walnuts.
Pour in greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and chicken.
Pour into casserole dish. Crush crackers and sprinkle over chicken.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Sprinkle poppy seed over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
